the Zolian Empire ten years ago.

00:10:30.731 --> 00:10:33.801 position:21% line:83% align:start
I can assure you that
our loyalty remains steadfast.

00:10:33.834 --> 00:10:35.236 position:30% line:89% align:start
I know it does.

00:10:35.269 --> 00:10:37.138 position:38% line:83% align:start
OFFICER:
He has arrived, my lord.

00:10:37.171 --> 00:10:39.940 position:13% line:83% align:start
This salt mine-- I was told
you were once the supervisor.

00:10:39.974 --> 00:10:42.710 position:16% line:83% align:start
-Is that correct, Tohlim?
-Correct.

00:10:42.743 --> 00:10:45.746 position:10% line:83% align:start
YOTALU: I'd like you to guide
someone through it.

00:10:48.482 --> 00:10:50.985 position:35% line:83% align:start
Halt! Halt!
All entry is forbidden.

00:10:51.018 --> 00:10:52.386 position:30% line:89% align:start
(horse neighs)

00:10:52.419 --> 00:10:55.356 position:10% line:83% align:start
Foolish lout! Do you not know
to whom you speak?

00:10:55.389 --> 00:10:58.692 position:24% line:83% align:start
-He has come to...
-Makokan, that's enough.

00:10:58.726 --> 00:11:00.895 position:21% line:89% align:start
You're overreacting.

00:11:00.928 --> 00:11:03.330 position:19% line:83% align:start
-SOLDIER: Who are you?
-(groans)

00:11:03.364 --> 00:11:04.899 position:16% line:89% align:start
The man before you is...

00:11:04.932 --> 00:11:06.400 position:21% line:89% align:start
Don't make that face.

00:11:06.433 --> 00:11:08.402 position:24% line:89% align:start
YOTALU: Stand down.

00:11:08.435 --> 00:11:10.404 position:24% line:89% align:start
GUARD: Lord Yotalu.

00:11:13.174 --> 00:11:15.309 position:21% line:83% align:start
Thank you for coming
on such short notice.

00:11:15.342 --> 00:11:17.311 position:30% line:83% align:start
Please, there's
no need for that.

00:11:17.344 --> 00:11:19.180 position:16% line:89% align:start
Let me introduce Tohlim.

00:11:19.213 --> 00:11:21.815 position:16% line:83% align:start
He is the right-hand man
to the king of Aquafa.

00:11:25.019 --> 00:11:27.254 position:19% line:89% align:start
I am Hohsalle Yuguraul.

00:11:27.288 --> 00:11:29.456 position:10% line:89% align:start
It's a pleasure to meet you.

00:11:29.490 --> 00:11:32.059 position:21% line:83% align:start
Sir Hohsalle, you are
one of the sacred doctors.

00:11:32.092 --> 00:11:34.862 position:27% line:83% align:start
I consider making
your acquaintance a great honor.

00:11:34.895 --> 00:11:36.764 position:16% line:89% align:start
The pleasure is all mine.

00:11:36.797 --> 00:11:38.866 position:30% line:83% align:start
You do yourself
a disservice, sir.

00:11:38.899 --> 00:11:42.069 position:16% line:83% align:start
Your political acumen is
as impressive as it is reliable.

00:11:42.102 --> 00:11:44.805 position:21% line:83% align:start
But I truly thank you
for the kind words.

00:11:45.806 --> 00:11:47.074 position:21% line:89% align:start
Do I detect sarcasm?

00:11:47.107 --> 00:11:49.243 position:19% line:89% align:start
(chuckles) Not at all.

00:11:51.245 --> 00:11:53.881 position:27% line:83% align:start
I beg your pardon
if this seems cold,

00:11:53.914 --> 00:11:56.784 position:24% line:83% align:start
but could you delay
the cremation, Lord Yotalu?

00:11:56.817 --> 00:11:58.352 position:38% line:89% align:start
What for?

00:11:58.385 --> 00:12:00.955 position:10% line:83% align:start
HOHSALLE: I'd like to inspect
the bodies first.

00:12:00.988 --> 00:12:04.725 position:10% line:83% align:start
After all, that is the reason
I came all this way.

00:12:06.827 --> 00:12:08.796 position:21% line:89% align:start
(stammering, gasping)

00:12:08.829 --> 00:12:11.031 position:19% line:89% align:start
Wh-What are you doing?

00:12:11.065 --> 00:12:12.800 position:16% line:89% align:start
That boundary is sacred.

00:12:13.801 --> 00:12:16.003 position:35% line:89% align:start
(groaning)

00:12:17.539 --> 00:12:19.740 position:38% line:83% align:start
HOHSALLE:
Mikimu, please.

00:12:21.842 --> 00:12:23.911 position:38% line:83% align:start
SOLDIER:
That's Sir Hohsalle, huh?

00:12:23.944 --> 00:12:26.514 position:7% line:83% align:start
SOLDIER 2: Priest-doctors can't
compete with Zol's physician.

00:12:26.548 --> 00:12:30.985 position:7% line:83% align:start
Especially since he apparently
saved Lord Yotalu's mother.

00:12:31.018 --> 00:12:33.220 position:30% line:83% align:start
I guess keeping
the second-empress alive

00:12:33.254 --> 00:12:34.822 position:27% line:89% align:start
would win trust.

00:12:52.306 --> 00:12:54.041 position:38% line:89% align:start
(gasping)

00:12:56.443 --> 00:12:59.213 position:30% line:83% align:start
-Sir Hohsalle.
-Yes. Bring them, please.

00:12:59.246 --> 00:13:01.048 position:41% line:89% align:start
Right.

00:13:02.550 --> 00:13:03.784 position:38% line:89% align:start
(grunts)

00:13:08.590 --> 00:13:11.058 position:24% line:89% align:start
(gasping, exhales)

00:13:13.394 --> 00:13:16.130 position:7% line:83% align:start
-HOHSALLE: Take a look at this.
-YOTALU: Just as I suspected.

00:13:16.163 --> 00:13:18.966 position:7% line:83% align:start
The falconry party was attacked
by the same dogs?

00:13:18.999 --> 00:13:21.302 position:16% line:83% align:start
HOHSALLE: Yes. They bear
the same bite marks.

00:13:21.335 --> 00:13:23.103 position:21% line:83% align:start
However, these aren't
the only patients

00:13:23.137 --> 00:13:24.972 position:10% line:89% align:start
I've seen with these lesions.

00:13:25.005 --> 00:13:29.176 position:13% line:83% align:start
My brother, are you saying
he has the same disease?

00:13:29.209 --> 00:13:31.579 position:35% line:89% align:start
What is it?

00:13:31.613 --> 00:13:35.316 position:7% line:89% align:start
I wasn't sure until now, but...

00:13:35.349 --> 00:13:38.787 position:19% line:83% align:start
It's black wolf fever,
also known as mittsual.

00:13:39.654 --> 00:13:41.422 position:19% line:89% align:start
(priests gasp, whimper)

00:13:41.455 --> 00:13:43.457 position:33% line:89% align:start
The mittsual?

00:13:46.661 --> 00:13:49.196 position:38% line:83% align:start
HOHSALLE:
All of them are Zolians?

00:13:49.229 --> 00:13:51.932 position:10% line:89% align:start
Condemned criminals, but yes.

00:13:51.965 --> 00:13:55.035 position:21% line:83% align:start
The people of Aquafa
consider this a sacred place.

00:13:55.069 --> 00:13:57.905 position:27% line:83% align:start
It would be wrong
to make them work here.

00:13:59.139 --> 00:14:00.542 position:38% line:83% align:start
HOHSALLE:
Hardly any stench.

00:14:00.575 --> 00:14:02.943 position:21% line:83% align:start
The bodies down here
are in better condition.

00:14:02.976 --> 00:14:05.312 position:7% line:83% align:start
Could we take some of them back
to the capital with us?

00:14:05.346 --> 00:14:07.014 position:41% line:83% align:start
YOTALU:
I'm sure the priest-doctors

00:14:07.047 --> 00:14:08.882 position:16% line:89% align:start
won't be happy about it.

00:14:08.916 --> 00:14:10.351 position:30% line:89% align:start
But very well.

00:14:10.384 --> 00:14:12.386 position:24% line:83% align:start
-It shall be done.
-Huh?

00:14:14.188 --> 00:14:15.557 position:38% line:89% align:start
(grunts)

00:14:15.590 --> 00:14:17.991 position:16% line:83% align:start
There's nothing to fear.
She's one of ours.

00:14:18.025 --> 00:14:20.861 position:10% line:83% align:start
I asked her to come down here
to inspect things.

00:14:24.699 --> 00:14:26.367 position:21% line:89% align:start
What have you found?

00:14:26.400 --> 00:14:28.435 position:38% line:83% align:start
Somehow,
one of the workers managed

00:14:28.469 --> 00:14:30.437 position:10% line:89% align:start
to make it out of here alive.

00:14:30.471 --> 00:14:31.673 position:38% line:83% align:start
HOHSALLE:
Hmm.

00:14:31.706 --> 00:14:33.040 position:24% line:89% align:start
It's been smashed.

00:14:33.073 --> 00:14:34.576 position:16% line:83% align:start
Could that have been done
by a human?

00:14:34.609 --> 00:14:37.579 position:21% line:83% align:start
SAE: He was bitten by
one of the dogs, though.

00:14:37.612 --> 00:14:39.980 position:13% line:83% align:start
That caused him to collapse
for a moment.

00:14:40.013 --> 00:14:43.150 position:7% line:83% align:start
Then he got back onto his feet,
broke out and went that way.

00:14:43.183 --> 00:14:45.386 position:16% line:83% align:start
Hey! I asked you if this
could've been done by...

00:14:45.419 --> 00:14:47.187 position:19% line:89% align:start
Makokan, let her work.

00:14:47.221 --> 00:14:50.457 position:24% line:83% align:start
A chain was dragged
across the floor here.

00:14:50.491 --> 00:14:52.226 position:13% line:89% align:start
And there are bloodstains.

00:14:52.259 --> 00:14:54.529 position:24% line:83% align:start
But the footprints
leading away suggest

00:14:54.562 --> 00:14:57.164 position:13% line:83% align:start
that he wasn't carried out
of this mine by a dog.

00:14:59.634 --> 00:15:02.436 position:21% line:83% align:start
He walked to the exit
by his own two feet.

00:15:04.171 --> 00:15:06.140 position:19% line:89% align:start
You said he was bitten.

00:15:06.173 --> 00:15:08.041 position:24% line:83% align:start
Are you sure that's
where the blood came from?

00:15:08.075 --> 00:15:10.344 position:24% line:83% align:start
This pool of blood
was fairly sizable.

00:15:10.377 --> 00:15:13.280 position:19% line:83% align:start
And the shape certainly
suggests a bite.

00:15:13.313 --> 00:15:15.115 position:19% line:89% align:start
Should that concern us?

00:15:17.151 --> 00:15:18.620 position:7% line:89% align:start
If this man did indeed survive

00:15:18.653 --> 00:15:21.288 position:24% line:83% align:start
after being bitten
by one of those dogs,

00:15:21.321 --> 00:15:23.123 position:33% line:83% align:start
then there's
a strong possibility

00:15:23.157 --> 00:15:25.192 position:10% line:89% align:start
he's immune to the mittsual.

00:15:26.260 --> 00:15:28.195 position:30% line:83% align:start
Are you saying
if we could track them down,

00:15:28.228 --> 00:15:30.164 position:21% line:83% align:start
that might be enough
to figure out a cure?

00:15:30.197 --> 00:15:32.399 position:24% line:83% align:start
If we had the blood
of a survivor

00:15:32.433 --> 00:15:35.068 position:10% line:89% align:start
and luck, yes, it's possible.

00:15:35.102 --> 00:15:37.705 position:13% line:83% align:start
YOTALU: Check the names of
all the slaves that were here.

00:15:37.739 --> 00:15:39.473 position:38% line:83% align:start
OFFICER:
M'lord.

00:15:44.077 --> 00:15:46.079 position:27% line:89% align:start
(yelling in pain)

00:15:48.115 --> 00:15:50.618 position:24% line:89% align:start
(grunts, whimpers)

00:15:59.126 --> 00:16:01.729 position:5% line:83% align:start
YOTALU: The Zolian army was once
thought invincible.

00:16:01.763 --> 00:16:03.531 position:16% line:83% align:start
Until they were wiped out
by the mittsual

00:16:03.565 --> 00:16:05.533 position:21% line:89% align:start
in a matter of days.

00:16:05.567 --> 00:16:07.602 position:21% line:89% align:start
And here it is again.

00:16:11.104 --> 00:16:13.474 position:38% line:77% align:start
OFFICER:
We've discovered the name
of the man who escaped.

00:16:13.508 --> 00:16:16.678 position:44% line:83% align:start
Van.
He came from the Gansa clan.

00:16:16.711 --> 00:16:18.613 position:35% line:89% align:start
Wait, Van?

00:16:18.646 --> 00:16:20.615 position:33% line:83% align:start
Where was he
when we took him prisoner?

00:16:20.648 --> 00:16:23.618 position:19% line:83% align:start
Records say we got him
at the battle of Kashuna River.

00:16:23.651 --> 00:16:26.253 position:16% line:89% align:start
(gasps) The Lone Antlers.

00:16:26.286 --> 00:16:28.322 position:24% line:89% align:start
Broken Antler Van.

00:16:28.355 --> 00:16:30.290 position:38% line:83% align:start
SOLDIER:
Lord Yotalu!

00:16:30.324 --> 00:16:33.393 position:16% line:89% align:start
Where is he? Lord Yotalu!

00:16:35.763 --> 00:16:37.998 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:16:54.081 --> 00:16:55.783 position:21% line:89% align:start
Then he still lives.

00:16:55.817 --> 00:16:59.521 position:5% line:83% align:start
To think, there was an Aquafaese
down there after all.

00:17:01.488 --> 00:17:03.290 position:16% line:89% align:start
She will find him for us.

00:17:03.323 --> 00:17:05.259 position:33% line:83% align:start
That woman is
the greatest tracker

00:17:05.292 --> 00:17:06.728 position:16% line:89% align:start
this land has ever known.

00:17:06.761 --> 00:17:08.295 position:27% line:89% align:start
Can you find him?

00:17:11.331 --> 00:17:12.600 position:38% line:89% align:start
She will.

00:17:12.634 --> 00:17:15.135 position:27% line:83% align:start
Be sure she knows
to bring him back to us alive.

00:17:15.168 --> 00:17:17.304 position:21% line:89% align:start
Yes, of course, sir.

00:17:19.139 --> 00:17:21.074 position:19% line:89% align:start
You heard Sir Hohsalle.

00:17:21.108 --> 00:17:23.711 position:35% line:83% align:start
We need you
to bring him back alive.

00:17:25.713 --> 00:17:27.682 position:27% line:83% align:start
That will not be
an easy task, sir.

00:17:27.715 --> 00:17:28.917 position:35% line:89% align:start
This Van is

00:17:28.950 --> 00:17:33.253 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>a surviving member</i>
 <i>of the elusive Lone Antlers.</i>

00:17:33.287 --> 00:17:35.055 position:27% line:89% align:start
(horse whinnies)

00:17:35.857 --> 00:17:37.457 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:17:37.491 --> 00:17:39.159 position:27% line:89% align:start
Wait! Come back!

00:17:39.192 --> 00:17:40.728 position:38% line:89% align:start
(groans)

00:17:43.130 --> 00:17:45.465 position:38% line:83% align:start
Hey, you.
How are you riding my pyuika?

00:17:45.499 --> 00:17:46.634 position:38% line:89% align:start
(grunts)

00:17:46.668 --> 00:17:48.335 position:44% line:89% align:start
Wow.

00:17:48.368 --> 00:17:51.706 position:5% line:83% align:start
You're the only person I've ever
seen mounted on one of those.

00:17:51.739 --> 00:17:53.841 position:10% line:89% align:start
Didn't think it was possible.

00:17:53.875 --> 00:17:55.843 position:7% line:89% align:start
There was a pack of ossam dogs

00:17:55.877 --> 00:17:58.646 position:19% line:83% align:start
that came flooding out
of the forest all of a sudden.

00:17:58.680 --> 00:18:00.648 position:16% line:89% align:start
They spooked the pyuika.

00:18:00.682 --> 00:18:02.717 position:10% line:83% align:start
It slipped free of its reins
and took off.

00:18:02.750 --> 00:18:05.252 position:21% line:83% align:start
Flipped my cart over
on top of me in the process.

00:18:05.285 --> 00:18:07.421 position:27% line:89% align:start
Well... (grunts)

00:18:07.454 --> 00:18:10.592 position:24% line:83% align:start
at least those dogs
didn't eat the poor beast.

00:18:10.625 --> 00:18:13.293 position:7% line:83% align:start
A healthy pyuika will fetch you
a king's ransom

00:18:13.327 --> 00:18:15.697 position:10% line:83% align:start
if you're willing to sell it
to the Zolian army.

00:18:15.730 --> 00:18:18.866 position:7% line:89% align:start
That's why I became a breeder.

00:18:18.900 --> 00:18:22.135 position:35% line:83% align:start
Of course,
that's easier said than done.

00:18:22.169 --> 00:18:25.339 position:21% line:83% align:start
All of mine are wild.
They won't obey my commands.

00:18:25.372 --> 00:18:27.575 position:24% line:83% align:start
I don't understand
what the Zolians want

00:18:27.609 --> 00:18:29.744 position:7% line:83% align:start
-with such stubborn creatures.
-Tasty.

00:18:29.777 --> 00:18:31.746 position:16% line:89% align:start
(chuckles) That's fahmu.

00:18:31.779 --> 00:18:34.147 position:16% line:89% align:start
It's a Zolian specialty.

00:18:34.181 --> 00:18:35.583 position:13% line:89% align:start
My wife baked them herself.

00:18:35.617 --> 00:18:38.620 position:5% line:83% align:start
-They're delicious, aren't they?
-(grunting)

00:18:38.653 --> 00:18:40.588 position:24% line:83% align:start
You know, if I were
to make a guess,

00:18:40.622 --> 00:18:42.757 position:21% line:83% align:start
I'd say it's because
the Zolians didn't know

00:18:42.790 --> 00:18:44.859 position:27% line:83% align:start
how to deal with
the Aquafaese pyuika riders

00:18:44.892 --> 00:18:47.528 position:21% line:89% align:start
during the last war.

00:18:47.562 --> 00:18:49.530 position:41% line:89% align:start
(sighs)

00:18:50.932 --> 00:18:53.901 position:24% line:83% align:start
MAN: You really are
something special, mister.

00:18:53.935 --> 00:18:56.738 position:7% line:83% align:start
I thought the one I already had
would calm down a little

00:18:56.771 --> 00:18:58.338 position:13% line:89% align:start
if I bought another female,

00:18:58.372 --> 00:19:00.642 position:21% line:83% align:start
so I decided to spend
what coin I had on me.

00:19:00.675 --> 00:19:02.744 position:10% line:89% align:start
But she's already with child.

00:19:04.712 --> 00:19:06.681 position:30% line:83% align:start
-Is she really?
-Mm.

00:19:06.714 --> 00:19:08.482 position:41% line:89% align:start
(sighs)

00:19:08.516 --> 00:19:11.485 position:27% line:83% align:start
These pyuika are
a complete mystery to me.

00:19:11.519 --> 00:19:14.454 position:10% line:83% align:start
I guess I should be thankful
for my injury.

00:19:14.488 --> 00:19:17.592 position:7% line:83% align:start
Or perhaps I should be thankful
for this little goddess, huh?

00:19:17.625 --> 00:19:20.528 position:38% line:83% align:start
-Yunacha!
-Huh? Yunacha?

00:19:20.561 --> 00:19:22.664 position:35% line:83% align:start
-VAN: Yuna.
-(Yuna chuckles)

00:19:22.697 --> 00:19:25.198 position:19% line:89% align:start
That's her name. Yuna.

00:19:25.232 --> 00:19:27.434 position:47% line:89% align:start
Ah.

00:19:27.467 --> 00:19:29.771 position:24% line:89% align:start
Gotcha. I'm Tohma.

00:19:31.806 --> 00:19:33.473 position:38% line:89% align:start
I'm Van.

00:19:33.508 --> 00:19:34.909 position:41% line:83% align:start
TOHMA:
Yuna and Van.

00:19:34.942 --> 00:19:37.477 position:19% line:89% align:start
Well, I'm much obliged.

00:19:37.512 --> 00:19:40.648 position:7% line:83% align:start
Say, have you heard the latest
about the ossam dogs?

00:19:40.682 --> 00:19:43.685 position:16% line:83% align:start
Apparently, they attacked
the lord's falconry party.

00:19:43.718 --> 00:19:47.522 position:21% line:77% align:start
 <i>Whatever's happening</i>
 <i>with them,</i>
 <i>it sure doesn't bode well.</i>

00:19:47.555 --> 00:19:49.289 position:41% line:83% align:start
 <i>UTALU:</i>
 <i>Is it true?</i>

00:19:49.322 --> 00:19:51.959 position:13% line:89% align:start
Every one of them is dead?

00:19:51.993 --> 00:19:54.929 position:16% line:83% align:start
Yes. Slaves and soldiers,
for a total of 600.

00:19:54.962 --> 00:19:57.732 position:41% line:83% align:start
UTALU:
Killed by lowly dogs?

00:19:57.765 --> 00:20:00.768 position:7% line:89% align:start
Actually, Sir Hohsalle says...

00:20:00.802 --> 00:20:03.437 position:10% line:89% align:start
they contracted the mittsual.

00:20:03.470 --> 00:20:05.840 position:30% line:89% align:start
(gasps, sighs)

00:20:05.873 --> 00:20:07.842 position:21% line:89% align:start
The curse of Aquafa.

00:20:09.977 --> 00:20:11.646 position:16% line:89% align:start
In our grandfathers' era,

00:20:11.679 --> 00:20:13.715 position:27% line:83% align:start
the Zolian troops
who stormed this land

00:20:13.748 --> 00:20:15.750 position:16% line:89% align:start
fell prey to the disease.

00:20:15.783 --> 00:20:19.854 position:21% line:83% align:start
It was said to be the
retribution of dead Aquafaese.

00:20:19.887 --> 00:20:23.825 position:7% line:83% align:start
I wonder if it's a coincidence
that it's returned now,

00:20:23.858 --> 00:20:26.794 position:27% line:83% align:start
just in time for
the Emperor's Eyes visit.

00:20:26.828 --> 00:20:29.564 position:21% line:83% align:start
Forgive me, my lord,
but this curse

00:20:29.597 --> 00:20:31.498 position:30% line:83% align:start
is nothing more
than a superstition.

00:20:31.532 --> 00:20:33.868 position:10% line:83% align:start
The people of Aquafa pledged
our loyalty to you

00:20:33.901 --> 00:20:35.570 position:21% line:89% align:start
nearly ten years ago,

00:20:35.603 --> 00:20:37.572 position:24% line:83% align:start
and we would never
turn our backs on you.

00:20:37.605 --> 00:20:39.507 position:7% line:83% align:start
-UTALU: What of the Aquafaese?
-Uh...

00:20:39.540 --> 00:20:41.408 position:30% line:89% align:start
600 casualties.

00:20:41.441 --> 00:20:43.678 position:7% line:83% align:start
-Were any of them from Aquafa?
-AQUAFA KING: Well, I...

00:20:43.711 --> 00:20:45.780 position:38% line:83% align:start
No, none.
But, brother, that doesn't...

00:20:45.813 --> 00:20:49.016 position:27% line:89% align:start
(Utalu grumbling)

00:20:50.017 --> 00:20:51.986 position:38% line:83% align:start
-(gasps)
-(Utalu grunting)

00:20:53.320 --> 00:20:54.789 position:41% line:89% align:start
(gasps)

00:20:55.790 --> 00:20:58.025 position:41% line:83% align:start
UTALU:
Tohlim.

00:20:58.059 --> 00:21:00.962 position:24% line:89% align:start
(grunts, chuckles)

00:21:00.995 --> 00:21:05.265 position:7% line:89% align:start
Loyal servant of Aquafa's king.

00:21:06.067 --> 00:21:08.368 position:35% line:89% align:start
(grunting)

00:21:09.402 --> 00:21:10.938 position:38% line:89% align:start
Lick it.

00:21:12.707 --> 00:21:15.910 position:16% line:83% align:start
Come over here and prove
the mittsual is no curse

00:21:15.943 --> 00:21:17.912 position:13% line:89% align:start
by contracting it yourself.

00:21:19.947 --> 00:21:21.549 position:21% line:89% align:start
As you wish, my lord.

00:21:30.792 --> 00:21:31.959 position:41% line:89% align:start
(gasps)

00:21:32.960 --> 00:21:34.529 position:38% line:89% align:start
(retches)

00:21:34.562 --> 00:21:35.963 position:38% line:89% align:start
Brother.

00:21:36.931 --> 00:21:38.900 position:33% line:89% align:start
Sir Hohsalle!

00:21:42.804 --> 00:21:44.972 position:35% line:89% align:start
(grunting)

00:21:45.006 --> 00:21:47.608 position:30% line:83% align:start
At this stage,
herbs won't be of any use.

00:21:47.642 --> 00:21:48.943 position:16% line:89% align:start
What can help him, then?

00:21:48.976 --> 00:21:50.745 position:5% line:89% align:start
I'll need to make an anti-poison

00:21:50.778 --> 00:21:52.880 position:21% line:83% align:start
by diluting the blood
of someone who was infected.

00:21:52.914 --> 00:21:55.883 position:21% line:83% align:start
Out of the question!
Lord Utalu's pure imperial blood

00:21:55.917 --> 00:21:58.886 position:24% line:83% align:start
must not be sullied
by that of a mere commoner.

00:21:58.920 --> 00:22:01.556 position:13% line:83% align:start
His survival is better left
for fate to decide.

00:22:01.589 --> 00:22:03.490 position:13% line:89% align:start
Bodies are not but vessels.

00:22:03.524 --> 00:22:06.493 position:13% line:83% align:start
Tainting Lord Utalu's soul
would be deplorable.

00:22:06.527 --> 00:22:08.495 position:21% line:83% align:start
-PRIESTS: Deplorable!
-UTALU: I need nothing.

00:22:08.529 --> 00:22:10.531 position:10% line:83% align:start
I shall heal this affliction
myself,

00:22:10.565 --> 00:22:12.399 position:19% line:89% align:start
without such medicine.

00:22:12.432 --> 00:22:14.101 position:16% line:89% align:start
Well spoken, Lord Utalu.

00:22:14.135 --> 00:22:16.504 position:5% line:83% align:start
There is nothing more imperative
than maintaining

00:22:16.537 --> 00:22:18.438 position:16% line:89% align:start
the purity of your soul.

00:22:19.439 --> 00:22:22.475 position:13% line:89% align:start
(Utalu groaning, wheezing)

00:22:24.846 --> 00:22:26.747 position:41% line:83% align:start
UTALU:
I shall not die.

00:22:27.849 --> 00:22:29.951 position:27% line:89% align:start
I shall not die.

00:22:29.984 --> 00:22:31.619 position:35% line:89% align:start
(straining)

00:22:35.723 --> 00:22:37.390 position:38% line:83% align:start
 <i>MAKOKAN:</i>
 <i>Is it true that Aquafaese</i>

00:22:37.424 --> 00:22:38.893 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>are immune to the mittsual?</i>

00:22:38.926 --> 00:22:41.929 position:7% line:83% align:start
That Zolians are the only ones
who can catch it?

00:22:41.963 --> 00:22:44.464 position:19% line:89% align:start
Some books say so, yes.

00:22:44.497 --> 00:22:46.033 position:16% line:89% align:start
Is something wrong, sir?

00:22:46.067 --> 00:22:48.970 position:7% line:83% align:start
I found Tohlim's calm demeanor
a bit peculiar.

00:22:49.003 --> 00:22:50.605 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Hmm.
-(chuckles)

00:22:50.638 --> 00:22:52.540 position:30% line:83% align:start
Well, a disease
certainly doesn't care

00:22:52.573 --> 00:22:54.374 position:16% line:89% align:start
what country you're from.

00:22:55.176 --> 00:22:56.811 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hmm.

00:22:56.844 --> 00:22:59.780 position:16% line:83% align:start
This Emperor's Eyes visit
is such nonsense.

00:22:59.814 --> 00:23:01.782 position:16% line:83% align:start
I know Fire Horse Village
is sacred,

00:23:01.816 --> 00:23:03.483 position:21% line:83% align:start
but why must they go
to the trouble

00:23:03.517 --> 00:23:05.485 position:33% line:83% align:start
of traveling
such a great distance?

00:23:05.519 --> 00:23:07.454 position:33% line:83% align:start
I think it's
because of the mittsual.

00:23:07.487 --> 00:23:10.591 position:7% line:83% align:start
It once forced the Zolian army
to retreat from there.

00:23:10.625 --> 00:23:12.860 position:10% line:83% align:start
They wish to reshape history,
I suppose,

00:23:12.894 --> 00:23:14.862 position:24% line:89% align:start
and to dispel fear.

00:23:14.896 --> 00:23:17.064 position:38% line:83% align:start
MAKOKAN:
In that case, it's a bit ironic

00:23:17.098 --> 00:23:19.867 position:19% line:83% align:start
that the mittsual would
return now, don't you think?

00:23:19.901 --> 00:23:23.037 position:38% line:77% align:start
HOHSALLE:
No. I suspect that's more
than coincidence.

00:23:23.070 --> 00:23:24.772 position:38% line:83% align:start
MAKOKAN:
Really? How so?

00:23:24.805 --> 00:23:26.874 position:16% line:83% align:start
HOHSALLE: You're not just
a swordsman anymore.

00:23:26.908 --> 00:23:28.776 position:30% line:89% align:start
Use your head.

00:23:30.511 --> 00:23:33.080 position:33% line:83% align:start
AQUAFA KING:
The falconry and the salt mine.

00:23:33.114 --> 00:23:36.183 position:19% line:83% align:start
So far, it's all going
according to plan.

00:23:36.217 --> 00:23:38.519 position:21% line:83% align:start
Once Yotalu succeeds
his brother,

00:23:38.552 --> 00:23:41.488 position:19% line:83% align:start
Zol will be much easier
to control.

00:23:41.522 --> 00:23:43.891 position:13% line:89% align:start
We're making good progress.

00:23:43.925 --> 00:23:47.995 position:13% line:83% align:start
And yet, we must be careful
not to move forward too hastily.

00:23:48.029 --> 00:23:49.664 position:41% line:83% align:start
OHFAN:
Are you afraid?

00:23:49.697 --> 00:23:52.199 position:21% line:83% align:start
Because at this rate,
the Emperor's Eyes

00:23:52.233 --> 00:23:55.870 position:7% line:83% align:start
are going to be at the doorstep
of my village as soon as spring.

00:23:55.903 --> 00:23:57.805 position:30% line:89% align:start
Have patience.

00:23:57.838 --> 00:24:01.108 position:10% line:83% align:start
One of the slaves in the mine
was Aquafaese.

00:24:02.109 --> 00:24:04.078 position:16% line:89% align:start
We must maintain secrecy,

00:24:04.111 --> 00:24:07.148 position:35% line:83% align:start
so proceed
with the utmost caution.

00:24:07.181 --> 00:24:10.685 position:10% line:83% align:start
OHFAN: I take no orders from
the spineless minions of Zol.

00:24:10.718 --> 00:24:12.186 position:33% line:89% align:start
Ohfan, wait.

00:24:12.219 --> 00:24:14.989 position:27% line:83% align:start
Is there a reason
for you to be so impatient?

00:24:19.193 --> 00:24:21.162 position:24% line:89% align:start
That's concerning.

00:24:21.195 --> 00:24:23.164 position:5% line:89% align:start
Are you certain we can trust him

00:24:23.197 --> 00:24:25.766 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>and Fire Horse Village</i>
 <i>to adhere to the plan?</i>

00:24:25.800 --> 00:24:27.768 position:38% line:83% align:start
 <i>TOHLIM:</i>
 <i>At the end of the day,</i>

00:24:27.802 --> 00:24:29.837 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>they are nothing more</i>
 <i>than our pawns.</i>

00:24:29.870 --> 00:24:32.640 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>The mittsual is</i>
 <i>their last lifeline.</i>

00:24:32.673 --> 00:24:35.776 position:35% line:83% align:start
 <i>They know</i>
 <i>they cannot act rashly.</i>

00:24:36.944 --> 00:24:39.080 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>AQUAFA KING: And what about</i>
 <i>this Aquafaese survivor</i>

00:24:39.113 --> 00:24:41.048 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>-from the salt mine?</i>
-(horse neighs)

00:24:41.082 --> 00:24:44.018 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>TOHLIM: We have a tracker</i>
 <i>working on finding him.</i>

00:24:44.051 --> 00:24:45.987 position:33% line:83% align:start
 <i>AQUAFA KING:</i>
 <i>Yes, but to what end?</i>

00:24:46.020 --> 00:24:47.822 position:38% line:83% align:start
 <i>TOHLIM:</i>
 <i>Leave that to me.</i>

00:24:47.855 --> 00:24:51.726 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>The life of one Aquafaese,</i>
 <i>or the future of</i>

00:24:51.759 --> 00:24:55.029 position:24% line:83% align:start
this entire land--
which would you choose?

00:24:55.062 --> 00:24:57.064 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hmm.

00:24:57.098 --> 00:24:59.499 position:27% line:89% align:start
That's checkmate.

00:25:03.104 --> 00:25:07.074 position:16% line:83% align:start
Obviously, you know what
my choice would be.

00:25:07.108 --> 00:25:09.510 position:41% line:83% align:start
TOHLIM:
As you wish.

00:25:19.787 --> 00:25:23.024 position:7% line:83% align:start
SAE: It's possible this man was
traveling with a small child.

00:25:23.057 --> 00:25:26.127 position:7% line:83% align:start
Ah. Yes, there was a young man
with an accent with them.

00:25:26.160 --> 00:25:28.929 position:10% line:89% align:start
Oh, the guy with the pyuika.

00:25:41.742 --> 00:25:43.778 position:27% line:83% align:start
-(birds chirping)
-(sheep bleating)

00:25:45.646 --> 00:25:48.015 position:35% line:83% align:start
-(grunting)
-TOHMA: Hey!

00:25:48.049 --> 00:25:50.785 position:30% line:89% align:start
Hey, I'm back!

00:25:50.818 --> 00:25:52.620 position:41% line:89% align:start
Tohma!

00:25:52.653 --> 00:25:53.821 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:25:54.822 --> 00:25:56.957 position:41% line:83% align:start
TOHMA:
Kiya!

00:26:03.831 --> 00:26:05.866 position:30% line:89% align:start
(quiet chatter)

00:26:07.701 --> 00:26:09.103 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:26:10.638 --> 00:26:13.074 position:41% line:83% align:start
TOHMA:
Hmm? Ah.

00:26:13.107 --> 00:26:15.342 position:19% line:89% align:start
(indistinct whispering)

00:26:15.376 --> 00:26:19.346 position:13% line:83% align:start
They want you to know that
they're grateful you saved me.

00:26:19.380 --> 00:26:20.881 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:26:20.915 --> 00:26:22.683 position:16% line:83% align:start
-(indistinct whispering)
-Oh, sure. Sorry.

00:26:22.716 --> 00:26:24.251 position:5% line:89% align:start
They can't speak to you directly

00:26:24.285 --> 00:26:26.720 position:21% line:83% align:start
until they've shared
a drink with you.

00:26:27.755 --> 00:26:28.923 position:38% line:89% align:start
(groans)

00:26:28.956 --> 00:26:31.092 position:33% line:83% align:start
-(chuckling)
-TOHMA: That's a great idea.

00:26:31.125 --> 00:26:33.828 position:21% line:83% align:start
Hey, if you'll let us
put you to work here,

00:26:33.861 --> 00:26:36.897 position:7% line:83% align:start
we can give you a place to stay
and all the food you can eat.

00:26:36.931 --> 00:26:38.966 position:24% line:89% align:start
Great. It's a deal.

00:26:38.999 --> 00:26:41.168 position:7% line:83% align:start
-Nobody knows pyuika like Van.
-(gasps)

00:26:41.202 --> 00:26:43.838 position:13% line:83% align:start
He'll be a big help to us,
I'll wager.

00:26:43.871 --> 00:26:45.840 position:38% line:83% align:start
-(gasps)
-(Yuna chuckles)

00:26:45.873 --> 00:26:47.842 position:27% line:83% align:start
-(mocking grunt)
-(gasps)

00:26:47.875 --> 00:26:49.810 position:41% line:83% align:start
TOHMA:
All right, that's settled.

00:26:49.844 --> 00:26:52.913 position:10% line:83% align:start
Enough with the formalities.
Let's drink!

00:26:56.450 --> 00:26:58.619 position:35% line:89% align:start
(slurping)

00:26:59.420 --> 00:27:00.855 position:47% line:89% align:start
Ah.

00:27:00.888 --> 00:27:02.323 position:19% line:89% align:start
Ah, that hit the spot!

00:27:02.356 --> 00:27:04.091 position:19% line:89% align:start
Drink up. Don't be shy.

00:27:04.125 --> 00:27:06.127 position:7% line:89% align:start
It is our tradition after all.

00:27:06.160 --> 00:27:07.862 position:7% line:83% align:start
-Ooh, she's a cute little tyke.
-(yawning)

00:27:07.895 --> 00:27:10.131 position:19% line:83% align:start
I don't really see much
of a resemblance, though.

00:27:10.164 --> 00:27:11.932 position:16% line:89% align:start
Takes after her mom? Oh.

00:27:11.966 --> 00:27:14.168 position:35% line:83% align:start
-Oh, dear.
-Uh...

00:27:15.336 --> 00:27:17.371 position:5% line:89% align:start
Where is she? Your wife, I mean.

00:27:17.404 --> 00:27:20.374 position:41% line:83% align:start
-Oh...
-Oh! Sorry. Tender subject, huh?

00:27:20.407 --> 00:27:21.842 position:27% line:89% align:start
(others gasping)

00:27:24.712 --> 00:27:26.780 position:16% line:89% align:start
You want to sit with me?

00:27:28.149 --> 00:27:29.783 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:27:30.784 --> 00:27:32.953 position:19% line:89% align:start
(Tohma yelping in pain)

00:27:34.788 --> 00:27:37.224 position:41% line:83% align:start
(sighs)
Well, that makes sense.

00:27:37.258 --> 00:27:40.261 position:21% line:83% align:start
Nothing beats sitting
on Daddy's lap, huh?

00:27:40.294 --> 00:27:41.896 position:44% line:89% align:start
Dada?

00:27:44.298 --> 00:27:45.366 position:35% line:89% align:start
Whoa, whoa.

00:27:45.399 --> 00:27:47.835 position:16% line:83% align:start
Sorry, but you won't get
any milk from Daddy's chest.

00:27:47.868 --> 00:27:50.237 position:30% line:83% align:start
You should try
giving her your finger.

00:27:55.809 --> 00:27:57.278 position:41% line:83% align:start
TOHMA:
Aw.

00:27:57.311 --> 00:27:59.180 position:24% line:83% align:start
-(stomach gurgling)
-(others gasp)

00:27:59.213 --> 00:28:00.347 position:35% line:89% align:start
(laughter)

00:28:00.381 --> 00:28:03.784 position:16% line:83% align:start
Sounds like she's not the
only one who needs some milk.

00:28:03.817 --> 00:28:07.188 position:27% line:83% align:start
In fact, I think
we should all eat.

00:28:07.221 --> 00:28:09.790 position:27% line:89% align:start
(birds squawking)

00:28:09.823 --> 00:28:11.392 position:44% line:83% align:start
AIDE:
His fever's come back.

00:28:11.425 --> 00:28:14.328 position:10% line:89% align:start
And his breathing is labored.

00:28:14.361 --> 00:28:17.064 position:27% line:89% align:start
(wheezing weakly)

00:28:19.366 --> 00:28:20.935 position:35% line:89% align:start
What is it?

00:28:20.968 --> 00:28:23.337 position:24% line:83% align:start
Not getting enough
from the herbs, are you?

00:28:25.906 --> 00:28:30.110 position:13% line:83% align:start
God save me from this hell,
I beg of you.

00:28:49.129 --> 00:28:51.265 position:41% line:89% align:start
(sighs)

00:28:57.539 --> 00:29:00.307 position:16% line:83% align:start
-Are you all right, sir?
-Fine.

00:29:00.341 --> 00:29:03.410 position:27% line:83% align:start
For generations,
we Yugurauls have served

00:29:03.444 --> 00:29:06.480 position:19% line:83% align:start
the leaders of the time
with our medical expertise,

00:29:06.514 --> 00:29:10.417 position:16% line:83% align:start
to learn about countries,
diseases and ourselves.

00:29:12.052 --> 00:29:14.989 position:19% line:83% align:start
But now, caught between
Aquafa and Zol,

00:29:15.022 --> 00:29:17.858 position:16% line:83% align:start
what can I possibly learn
about this illness?

00:29:18.993 --> 00:29:21.262 position:16% line:89% align:start
(sighs) Oh, I'm starving.

00:29:21.295 --> 00:29:22.997 position:10% line:89% align:start
Let's have rabbit for dinner.

00:29:23.030 --> 00:29:24.566 position:30% line:89% align:start
(aide panting)

00:29:24.599 --> 00:29:28.002 position:44% line:83% align:start
AIDE:
It's... Lord Utalu.

00:29:40.180 --> 00:29:42.283 position:41% line:83% align:start
TOHLIM:
Lord Yotalu.

00:29:42.316 --> 00:29:46.086 position:13% line:83% align:start
Perhaps we should postpone
the visit of the Emperor's Eyes.

00:29:46.120 --> 00:29:48.289 position:21% line:83% align:start
YOTALU: We sent word
of my brother's death,

00:29:48.322 --> 00:29:51.325 position:13% line:83% align:start
but the emperor is already
beyond the border.

00:30:06.273 --> 00:30:08.242 position:35% line:83% align:start
 <i>HOHSALLE:</i>
 <i>The mittsual.</i>

00:30:08.275 --> 00:30:10.177 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>I have to know more.</i>

00:30:11.211 --> 00:30:13.080 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>The man in the mine.</i>

00:30:14.915 --> 00:30:16.917 position:27% line:89% align:start
(birds chirping)

00:30:24.592 --> 00:30:26.827 position:35% line:89% align:start
(grunting)

00:30:29.997 --> 00:30:32.099 position:24% line:83% align:start
-Hey. Where's Dada?
-Huh?

00:30:32.132 --> 00:30:34.034 position:21% line:89% align:start
Oh. Uh, I don't know.

00:30:34.068 --> 00:30:36.837 position:7% line:83% align:start
-I haven't seen him in a while.
-(whimpers)

00:30:41.643 --> 00:30:43.844 position:27% line:89% align:start
(birds chirping)

00:30:49.249 --> 00:30:51.285 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:30:55.222 --> 00:30:57.057 position:44% line:83% align:start
VAN:
There it is.

00:30:57.091 --> 00:30:58.492 position:38% line:89% align:start
Asshimi.

00:30:58.526 --> 00:31:00.094 position:41% line:89% align:start
(gasps)

00:31:02.996 --> 00:31:04.365 position:41% line:89% align:start
(sighs)

00:31:05.366 --> 00:31:07.401 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:31:10.104 --> 00:31:11.639 position:35% line:89% align:start
(chopping)

00:31:17.144 --> 00:31:19.012 position:35% line:89% align:start
(grunting)

00:31:20.114 --> 00:31:22.316 position:35% line:89% align:start
(groaning)

00:31:25.419 --> 00:31:27.454 position:24% line:89% align:start
(groaning, gasping)

00:31:33.728 --> 00:31:36.096 position:38% line:89% align:start
(exhales)

00:31:41.969 --> 00:31:43.303 position:33% line:83% align:start
-YUNA: Dada!
-VAN'S SON: Father!

00:31:44.405 --> 00:31:45.673 position:38% line:89% align:start
It's you.

00:31:47.207 --> 00:31:49.143 position:24% line:89% align:start
Dada, I found you.

00:31:50.277 --> 00:31:52.279 position:27% line:89% align:start
Why are you here?

00:31:52.312 --> 00:31:54.081 position:35% line:89% align:start
(chuckles)

00:31:54.114 --> 00:31:56.917 position:24% line:83% align:start
I found you because
I can see you from anywhere.

00:31:57.685 --> 00:31:59.953 position:44% line:89% align:start
Wow.

00:31:59.987 --> 00:32:01.623 position:30% line:89% align:start
It's so pretty.

00:32:01.656 --> 00:32:04.224 position:21% line:89% align:start
Pretty? The asshimi?

00:32:04.258 --> 00:32:07.428 position:33% line:89% align:start
Yeah. Pretty.

00:32:12.466 --> 00:32:14.501 position:35% line:89% align:start
(straining)

00:32:17.104 --> 00:32:19.707 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:32:21.709 --> 00:32:23.711 position:27% line:83% align:start
-(grunts, laughs)
-Hey!

00:32:23.745 --> 00:32:26.113 position:33% line:83% align:start
YOKI (sighs):
What's the point of building

00:32:26.146 --> 00:32:28.115 position:13% line:89% align:start
this stupid thing, anyway?

00:32:28.148 --> 00:32:30.317 position:24% line:83% align:start
A pyuika could leap
over this, no problem.

00:32:30.350 --> 00:32:32.152 position:30% line:83% align:start
-(boy laughing)
-Huh?

00:32:33.220 --> 00:32:35.155 position:35% line:83% align:start
Stop that!
It's not safe over here.

00:32:35.189 --> 00:32:36.356 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Huh?
-Huh?

00:32:39.727 --> 00:32:40.895 position:41% line:83% align:start
TOHMA:
Let me help you.

00:32:42.296 --> 00:32:44.699 position:10% line:83% align:start
VAN: This will give the whole
fence the scent of asshimi.

00:32:44.732 --> 00:32:46.534 position:33% line:89% align:start
(Yuna sniffs)

00:32:51.171 --> 00:32:52.707 position:41% line:83% align:start
TOHMA:
That's Olaha.

00:32:52.740 --> 00:32:55.008 position:10% line:89% align:start
It means "born at daybreak."

00:32:55.042 --> 00:32:57.211 position:24% line:83% align:start
That one's very old
and stubborn, though.

00:32:57.244 --> 00:32:59.112 position:30% line:89% align:start
Hard to handle.

00:32:59.146 --> 00:33:01.181 position:35% line:89% align:start
(whistling)

00:33:03.150 --> 00:33:05.385 position:41% line:83% align:start
TOHMA:
Hey, that's dangerous.

00:33:07.120 --> 00:33:08.690 position:21% line:89% align:start
(gasps) He wouldn't.

00:33:10.224 --> 00:33:11.492 position:38% line:89% align:start
(squeals)

00:33:11.526 --> 00:33:12.993 position:16% line:89% align:start
(Kiya and Tohma gasping)

00:33:19.466 --> 00:33:21.468 position:38% line:89% align:start
(gasping)

00:33:27.609 --> 00:33:29.511 position:38% line:89% align:start
(gasping)

00:33:34.348 --> 00:33:35.717 position:35% line:89% align:start
(whistles)

00:33:35.750 --> 00:33:37.417 position:38% line:89% align:start
(gasping)

00:33:41.488 --> 00:33:42.790 position:41% line:83% align:start
TOHMA:
What did I tell you?

00:33:42.824 --> 00:33:44.659 position:24% line:89% align:start
This guy's amazing.

00:33:44.692 --> 00:33:46.393 position:5% line:89% align:start
Before long, he's gonna bring in

00:33:46.426 --> 00:33:48.663 position:19% line:83% align:start
a big old pile of cash
from the Zolian army.

00:33:48.696 --> 00:33:51.298 position:44% line:83% align:start
OHMA:
You greedy fool.

00:33:58.238 --> 00:34:00.207 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:34:00.240 --> 00:34:01.609 position:38% line:89% align:start
(grunts)

00:34:12.185 --> 00:34:14.187 position:41% line:89% align:start
(sighs)

00:34:16.189 --> 00:34:18.191 position:38% line:89% align:start
(grunts)

00:34:31.138 --> 00:34:33.106 position:24% line:83% align:start
-(hunters yelling)
-HUNTER: Come on!

00:34:33.140 --> 00:34:35.442 position:33% line:83% align:start
-(clattering)
-(yelling continues)

00:34:39.179 --> 00:34:41.616 position:38% line:83% align:start
-Get him!
-(yelling continues)

00:34:43.585 --> 00:34:46.486 position:35% line:89% align:start
(grunting)

00:34:48.488 --> 00:34:50.658 position:21% line:89% align:start
(screams) Oh, my leg!

00:34:50.692 --> 00:34:52.527 position:44% line:89% align:start
Shh.

00:34:52.560 --> 00:34:55.395 position:41% line:83% align:start
TOHMA:
Van! It's coming your way!

00:34:55.429 --> 00:34:56.864 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Huh?
-Hmm?

00:34:56.898 --> 00:34:58.365 position:44% line:83% align:start
YUNA:
Dada.

00:35:04.404 --> 00:35:06.206 position:30% line:89% align:start
(gasps softly)

00:35:06.239 --> 00:35:07.642 position:41% line:89% align:start
(gasps)

00:35:12.680 --> 00:35:15.215 position:38% line:83% align:start
-(gasps)
-(blowing)

00:35:15.248 --> 00:35:16.751 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:35:17.752 --> 00:35:18.886 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:35:28.796 --> 00:35:30.464 position:35% line:89% align:start
(squealing)

00:35:30.497 --> 00:35:32.399 position:38% line:89% align:start
(screams)

00:35:40.642 --> 00:35:43.276 position:21% line:89% align:start
(gasping, chuckling)

00:35:45.880 --> 00:35:48.215 position:27% line:83% align:start
-Well done, Van.
-I can't believe it.

00:35:48.248 --> 00:35:49.651 position:33% line:83% align:start
-Incredible.
-Amazing.

00:35:49.684 --> 00:35:52.419 position:19% line:83% align:start
-YOKI: Just incredible!
-(groans)

00:35:54.354 --> 00:35:56.791 position:41% line:89% align:start
(sighs)

00:35:56.824 --> 00:35:58.425 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:36:00.293 --> 00:36:01.796 position:35% line:89% align:start
(chuckling)

00:36:01.829 --> 00:36:03.831 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:36:29.624 --> 00:36:31.659 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:36:55.583 --> 00:36:57.885 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:37:20.508 --> 00:37:22.476 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:37:39.527 --> 00:37:41.562 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:38:05.753 --> 00:38:08.656 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:38:17.364 --> 00:38:19.399 position:24% line:89% align:start
(insects chirping)

00:38:31.378 --> 00:38:33.614 position:35% line:83% align:start
-Now what?
-I'm gonna drink it.

00:38:33.648 --> 00:38:35.716 position:16% line:89% align:start
You can drink that stuff?

00:38:35.750 --> 00:38:37.084 position:47% line:89% align:start
Oh.

00:38:37.118 --> 00:38:38.686 position:21% line:89% align:start
You're good at that.

00:38:38.719 --> 00:38:39.854 position:27% line:89% align:start
(chuckles) Yeah.

00:38:39.887 --> 00:38:42.056 position:30% line:83% align:start
I always did it
for Mama at home.

00:38:42.089 --> 00:38:44.091 position:35% line:89% align:start
Oh. Really?

00:38:44.125 --> 00:38:46.694 position:21% line:89% align:start
Just like old times.

00:38:46.727 --> 00:38:47.995 position:33% line:89% align:start
Pyuika milk.

00:38:49.063 --> 00:38:50.198 position:5% line:89% align:start
My brothers and sisters and I...

00:38:50.231 --> 00:38:52.700 position:41% line:77% align:start
-Here.
-...used to fight over it
when we were young.

00:38:52.733 --> 00:38:54.068 position:38% line:89% align:start
(groans)

00:38:54.101 --> 00:38:56.771 position:44% line:83% align:start
OHMA:
I'd completely forgotten.

00:38:56.804 --> 00:39:00.541 position:7% line:83% align:start
Many years ago, the Zolian army
came through here

00:39:00.575 --> 00:39:04.411 position:10% line:83% align:start
and laid waste to everything,
scaring all the pyuika away.

00:39:04.444 --> 00:39:06.681 position:19% line:89% align:start
Just the mention of Zol

00:39:06.714 --> 00:39:08.115 position:19% line:83% align:start
would send us trembling
and running for cover.

00:39:08.149 --> 00:39:09.550 position:13% line:89% align:start
Hey! Don't drink all of it!

00:39:09.584 --> 00:39:12.653 position:21% line:83% align:start
But that all changed
about ten years ago.

00:39:12.687 --> 00:39:15.455 position:16% line:83% align:start
A group of pyuika riders
called the Lone Antlers

00:39:15.488 --> 00:39:19.727 position:5% line:83% align:start
took up arms against the Zolians
and became Aquafa's guardians.

00:39:19.760 --> 00:39:22.129 position:19% line:83% align:start
It was because of them
that Zol was willing

00:39:22.163 --> 00:39:24.131 position:7% line:89% align:start
to enter into a treaty with us.

00:39:24.165 --> 00:39:26.133 position:30% line:83% align:start
And now we have
wonderful Zolian wives

00:39:26.167 --> 00:39:29.770 position:10% line:83% align:start
-to bake us delicious fahmu.
-Here, have some.

00:39:29.804 --> 00:39:33.040 position:10% line:89% align:start
None for me, dear, thank you.

00:39:33.074 --> 00:39:35.676 position:10% line:83% align:start
Zolians believe that drinking
the milk of a beast

00:39:35.710 --> 00:39:37.477 position:33% line:83% align:start
will turn you
into a beast yourself.

00:39:37.511 --> 00:39:38.679 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:39:38.713 --> 00:39:41.682 position:44% line:83% align:start
VAN:
I was hunting a long time ago,

00:39:41.716 --> 00:39:44.886 position:7% line:83% align:start
and I saw a herd of pyuika get
attacked by a pack of wolves.

00:39:44.919 --> 00:39:48.488 position:10% line:83% align:start
One of the fawns wasn't quick
enough to keep up with the herd,

00:39:48.522 --> 00:39:50.892 position:19% line:83% align:start
so it was left to deal
with the wolves all by itself.

00:39:50.925 --> 00:39:52.560 position:38% line:83% align:start
-(grunts)
-(chuckling)

00:39:52.593 --> 00:39:54.629 position:16% line:83% align:start
VAN: But then an old buck
leapt forward to protect it.

00:39:54.662 --> 00:39:58.065 position:10% line:83% align:start
Stomped about to provoke them
and then ran off.

00:39:58.099 --> 00:40:01.903 position:13% line:83% align:start
I'd say an act like that is
befitting of the Deer King.

00:40:01.936 --> 00:40:04.805 position:27% line:83% align:start
Saving the fawn,
taking the brunt of the attack

00:40:04.839 --> 00:40:08.809 position:7% line:83% align:start
and vanishing into the forest--
did that make the buck a hero?

00:40:08.843 --> 00:40:11.946 position:21% line:83% align:start
Or was it just strong
and doing what needed to be done

00:40:11.979 --> 00:40:15.116 position:30% line:83% align:start
simply because
it needed to be done?

00:40:15.149 --> 00:40:17.084 position:10% line:89% align:start
That's how I saw it, anyway.

00:40:17.118 --> 00:40:18.753 position:24% line:89% align:start
The way I hear it,

00:40:18.786 --> 00:40:21.656 position:27% line:83% align:start
the Lone Antlers
are all dead and gone.

00:40:25.559 --> 00:40:27.995 position:24% line:83% align:start
When you leave us,
will you go alone?

00:40:28.029 --> 00:40:30.965 position:35% line:89% align:start
(laughter)

00:40:30.998 --> 00:40:34.135 position:44% line:83% align:start
VAN:
Yuna. Want to ride?

00:40:34.168 --> 00:40:35.569 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yeah.

00:40:37.805 --> 00:40:39.807 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:40:45.579 --> 00:40:47.615 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hyah!

00:40:50.518 --> 00:40:52.553 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:41:05.533 --> 00:41:06.834 position:44% line:83% align:start
YUNA:
What are those?

00:41:06.867 --> 00:41:08.836 position:44% line:83% align:start
VAN:
Wind flowers.

00:41:08.869 --> 00:41:10.671 position:44% line:83% align:start
YUNA:
And that?

00:41:10.705 --> 00:41:12.139 position:44% line:83% align:start
VAN:
A bush cricket.

00:41:12.173 --> 00:41:14.075 position:27% line:89% align:start
(bird screeches)

00:41:14.108 --> 00:41:16.243 position:44% line:83% align:start
YUNA:
And that?

00:41:16.277 --> 00:41:18.646 position:33% line:83% align:start
-(screeches)
-VAN: White-tailed eagle.

00:41:19.747 --> 00:41:21.282 position:44% line:83% align:start
YUNA:
Hmm.

00:41:21.315 --> 00:41:23.483 position:27% line:89% align:start
Then what's this?

00:41:25.553 --> 00:41:27.588 position:30% line:89% align:start
(laughs) Dada!

00:41:28.556 --> 00:41:30.858 position:30% line:89% align:start
(grunts, sighs)

00:41:30.891 --> 00:41:32.293 position:27% line:89% align:start
What about this?

00:41:32.326 --> 00:41:33.861 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yuna.

00:41:33.894 --> 00:41:35.596 position:38% line:89% align:start
(laughs)

00:41:35.629 --> 00:41:37.732 position:13% line:89% align:start
You know everything, Dada.

00:41:41.035 --> 00:41:42.870 position:44% line:83% align:start
VAN:
Do you like it here, Yuna?

00:41:42.903 --> 00:41:44.739 position:44% line:83% align:start
YUNA:
Where?

00:41:44.772 --> 00:41:46.741 position:44% line:83% align:start
VAN:
You like Tohma and his people?

00:41:46.774 --> 00:41:48.676 position:44% line:83% align:start
YUNA:
Yeah. I like everyone there.

00:41:49.710 --> 00:41:51.078 position:33% line:89% align:start
That's good.

00:41:51.112 --> 00:41:52.279 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:41:52.313 --> 00:41:54.048 position:30% line:89% align:start
And I like you.

00:41:55.082 --> 00:41:56.917 position:27% line:89% align:start
(sighs, chuckles)

00:41:58.919 --> 00:42:00.821 position:35% line:89% align:start
(whistles)

00:42:04.658 --> 00:42:06.527 position:33% line:89% align:start
(blows) Hmm?

00:42:09.163 --> 00:42:11.565 position:33% line:83% align:start
I'll make you
a deer whistle one day.

00:42:11.599 --> 00:42:13.067 position:33% line:89% align:start
(Yuna laughs)

00:42:25.913 --> 00:42:27.882 position:38% line:89% align:start
(neighs)

00:42:27.915 --> 00:42:29.183 position:27% line:89% align:start
Is that a pyuika?

00:42:29.216 --> 00:42:30.851 position:21% line:89% align:start
Those are quite rare.

00:42:30.885 --> 00:42:32.219 position:27% line:89% align:start
Hey, guess what.

00:42:32.253 --> 00:42:35.089 position:27% line:83% align:start
Dada's gonna make
a deer whistle for me.

00:42:35.122 --> 00:42:36.824 position:41% line:89% align:start
He is?

00:42:38.959 --> 00:42:40.661 position:27% line:89% align:start
Yuna, time to go.

00:42:40.694 --> 00:42:42.163 position:44% line:83% align:start
YUNA:
'Kay.

00:42:44.799 --> 00:42:46.167 position:30% line:89% align:start
(Yuna grunting)

00:42:52.139 --> 00:42:53.741 position:30% line:89% align:start
(Yuna chuckles)

00:42:55.109 --> 00:42:57.111 position:44% line:83% align:start
VAN:
Where are you headed?

00:42:57.144 --> 00:42:59.180 position:35% line:89% align:start
(Yuna coos)

00:43:08.989 --> 00:43:10.658 position:44% line:83% align:start
SAE:
May this country become

00:43:10.691 --> 00:43:12.827 position:33% line:83% align:start
a safe place
for orphans to live.

00:43:18.966 --> 00:43:21.001 position:21% line:89% align:start
(howling in distance)

00:43:24.872 --> 00:43:26.907 position:35% line:89% align:start
(rumbling)

00:43:38.452 --> 00:43:41.155 position:30% line:89% align:start
(grunts, gasps)

00:43:42.990 --> 00:43:44.358 position:38% line:89% align:start
(gasping)

00:43:50.998 --> 00:43:52.700 position:35% line:89% align:start
Found you.

00:43:52.733 --> 00:43:54.201 position:41% line:89% align:start
(gasps)

00:44:07.781 --> 00:44:09.150 position:38% line:89% align:start
(grunts)

00:44:09.183 --> 00:44:11.218 position:21% line:89% align:start
Quick! Get a move on!

00:44:11.252 --> 00:44:14.288 position:13% line:83% align:start
Van's gonna get ahead of us
if we don't pick up the pace.

00:44:15.756 --> 00:44:17.658 position:30% line:89% align:start
(boy laughing)

00:44:19.460 --> 00:44:21.162 position:21% line:89% align:start
Huh? That's unusual.

00:44:21.195 --> 00:44:22.930 position:30% line:89% align:start
A Zolian rider.

00:44:27.168 --> 00:44:29.069 position:30% line:89% align:start
(grunts, gasps)

00:44:32.206 --> 00:44:33.774 position:44% line:89% align:start
Whoa.

00:44:33.807 --> 00:44:35.809 position:35% line:89% align:start
(neighing)

00:44:37.811 --> 00:44:39.046 position:24% line:89% align:start
What's the matter?

00:44:41.081 --> 00:44:42.917 position:30% line:83% align:start
RIDER (weakly):
Dogs.

00:44:42.950 --> 00:44:45.386 position:21% line:89% align:start
They were black dogs.

00:44:45.419 --> 00:44:47.454 position:38% line:89% align:start
(gasping)

00:44:48.889 --> 00:44:51.825 position:19% line:89% align:start
What's happening, Dada?

00:44:51.859 --> 00:44:53.027 position:35% line:89% align:start
Stay back!

00:44:53.060 --> 00:44:54.962 position:38% line:89% align:start
(gasping)

00:44:57.298 --> 00:44:58.832 position:35% line:83% align:start
 <i>HOHSALLE:</i>
 <i>The mittsual struck another</i>

00:44:58.866 --> 00:45:00.234 position:30% line:89% align:start
Zolian village?

00:45:01.168 --> 00:45:02.770 position:21% line:89% align:start
Was there an inquest?

00:45:02.803 --> 00:45:04.205 position:27% line:89% align:start
No, there wasn't.

00:45:04.238 --> 00:45:06.941 position:19% line:83% align:start
The priest-doctors had
all the bodies cremated.

00:45:06.974 --> 00:45:09.210 position:7% line:83% align:start
Then they prayed for three days
and three nights.

00:45:09.243 --> 00:45:10.411 position:41% line:89% align:start
(sighs)

00:45:10.444 --> 00:45:13.113 position:24% line:83% align:start
This isn't a curse.
It's a disease.

00:45:14.114 --> 00:45:16.150 position:27% line:89% align:start
 <i>Think, Hohsalle.</i>

00:45:16.183 --> 00:45:19.019 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>Why does it seem to be</i>
 <i>targeting Zol and not Aquafa?</i>

00:45:19.053 --> 00:45:20.888 position:35% line:83% align:start
(panting):
Sir Hohsalle!

00:45:20.921 --> 00:45:22.823 position:21% line:89% align:start
We... we've done it.

00:45:22.856 --> 00:45:25.059 position:16% line:89% align:start
Hush. This is a library.

00:45:25.092 --> 00:45:27.194 position:16% line:83% align:start
You've discovered a cure
for the mittsual?

00:45:27.228 --> 00:45:29.830 position:27% line:89% align:start
Yes. Uh, uh, no.

00:45:29.863 --> 00:45:32.366 position:16% line:83% align:start
What I mean is it appears
we've found the Lone Antler.

00:45:32.399 --> 00:45:34.368 position:21% line:83% align:start
The one who survived
the salt mine.

00:45:34.401 --> 00:45:36.103 position:27% line:83% align:start
-HOHSALLE: What?
-(man grumbles)

00:45:37.271 --> 00:45:39.541 position:13% line:83% align:start
The tracker woman sent word
of his whereabouts.

00:45:39.574 --> 00:45:42.376 position:7% line:83% align:start
Lord Tohlim personally rode out
with his troops to go catch him.

00:45:42.409 --> 00:45:44.078 position:7% line:89% align:start
Tohlim himself is going there?

00:45:44.111 --> 00:45:45.980 position:27% line:89% align:start
Get your things.

00:45:46.013 --> 00:45:48.048 position:7% line:89% align:start
We're going after that old man.

00:45:48.082 --> 00:45:49.416 position:38% line:83% align:start
MAKOKAN:
Huh?

00:45:49.450 --> 00:45:51.085 position:38% line:83% align:start
HOHSALLE:
This bodes ill.

00:45:53.053 --> 00:45:56.190 position:13% line:83% align:start
YOKI: Some believe the gods
set the ossam upon Zol

00:45:56.223 --> 00:46:00.261 position:16% line:83% align:start
and killed Lord Utalu as
punishment for scorning Aquafa.

00:46:00.294 --> 00:46:02.263 position:13% line:83% align:start
Whether that's true or not,
it's causing

00:46:02.296 --> 00:46:04.098 position:13% line:89% align:start
a great deal of resentment.

00:46:07.234 --> 00:46:09.270 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:46:22.316 --> 00:46:24.318 position:21% line:89% align:start
(explosive whooshing)

00:46:32.159 --> 00:46:35.362 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>TOHMA: There's no such thing</i>
 <i>as Aquafa or Zol.</i>

00:46:35.396 --> 00:46:37.431 position:21% line:89% align:start
We're all one family.

00:46:37.464 --> 00:46:39.933 position:44% line:83% align:start
OHMA:
Indeed.

00:46:39.967 --> 00:46:43.070 position:13% line:83% align:start
Our people have lived here
for generations.

00:46:43.103 --> 00:46:44.305 position:30% line:89% align:start
It is our home.

00:46:44.338 --> 00:46:47.141 position:38% line:83% align:start
And more,
this place is our motherland.

00:46:47.174 --> 00:46:49.977 position:30% line:83% align:start
-(Tohma sighs)
-(Van grunts)

00:46:50.010 --> 00:46:52.379 position:19% line:89% align:start
Huh? What's the matter?

00:46:52.413 --> 00:46:54.381 position:44% line:83% align:start
VAN:
Watch Yuna.

00:46:54.415 --> 00:46:56.317 position:21% line:89% align:start
Huh? Where you going?

00:46:56.350 --> 00:47:00.187 position:13% line:83% align:start
If they ask, just tell them
I forced you to give me shelter.

00:47:00.220 --> 00:47:03.023 position:33% line:89% align:start
W-Wait. Van!

00:47:18.573 --> 00:47:20.441 position:41% line:83% align:start
TOHLIM:
Van of the Lone Antlers.

00:47:20.474 --> 00:47:23.277 position:13% line:83% align:start
The people of this village
know nothing.

00:47:23.310 --> 00:47:27.348 position:21% line:83% align:start
As long as you don't
involve them, I'll come quietly.

00:47:28.349 --> 00:47:29.517 position:41% line:83% align:start
TOHLIM:
Very well.

00:47:35.356 --> 00:47:38.158 position:27% line:89% align:start
The Lone Antlers?

00:47:38.192 --> 00:47:40.027 position:41% line:83% align:start
-Dada?
-Shh.

00:47:40.060 --> 00:47:42.496 position:30% line:83% align:start
-Where's Dada?
-(all gasping)

00:47:42.530 --> 00:47:44.331 position:44% line:89% align:start
Dada!

00:47:44.365 --> 00:47:45.866 position:35% line:89% align:start
Stay there.

00:47:47.334 --> 00:47:48.469 position:24% line:89% align:start
(whimpers, grunts)

00:47:48.502 --> 00:47:50.304 position:33% line:89% align:start
You bastard.

00:47:50.337 --> 00:47:51.639 position:44% line:89% align:start
Dada!

00:47:52.640 --> 00:47:55.209 position:35% line:89% align:start
(straining)

00:47:55.242 --> 00:47:57.545 position:30% line:89% align:start
(gasps, grunts)

00:48:01.982 --> 00:48:04.652 position:33% line:83% align:start
Van, what...
what's a Lone Antler?

00:48:04.686 --> 00:48:06.654 position:41% line:83% align:start
TOHLIM:
What did you just do, Van?

00:48:06.688 --> 00:48:09.356 position:30% line:83% align:start
It just turned
into a tree and...

00:48:09.390 --> 00:48:10.991 position:38% line:89% align:start
(gasping)

00:48:11.024 --> 00:48:12.259 position:44% line:83% align:start
YUNA:
Dada!

00:48:12.292 --> 00:48:14.529 position:41% line:83% align:start
TOHLIM:
Come quietly.

00:48:19.667 --> 00:48:22.469 position:44% line:83% align:start
YUNA:
When will you be back?

00:48:22.504 --> 00:48:25.439 position:44% line:83% align:start
Wait.
Dada, when will you be back?

00:48:36.684 --> 00:48:39.119 position:33% line:83% align:start
-(whooshing)
-(growling)

00:48:40.087 --> 00:48:41.989 position:19% line:89% align:start
(frightened whimpering)

00:48:42.022 --> 00:48:44.324 position:35% line:89% align:start
(screaming)

00:48:47.394 --> 00:48:49.697 position:41% line:83% align:start
 <i>VOICE:</i>
 <i>Ah. Got you.</i>

00:48:49.731 --> 00:48:51.331 position:35% line:89% align:start
(grunting)

00:48:53.300 --> 00:48:54.435 position:38% line:83% align:start
SOLDIER:
Ossam!

00:48:54.468 --> 00:48:55.670 position:35% line:83% align:start
SOLDIER 2:
We're surrounded!

00:48:55.703 --> 00:48:57.271 position:35% line:83% align:start
SOLDIER 3:
It's the dogs again!

00:48:57.304 --> 00:48:58.673 position:35% line:83% align:start
SOLDIER 4:
What are they doing here?

00:48:58.706 --> 00:49:00.441 position:38% line:89% align:start
Fear not.

00:49:00.474 --> 00:49:02.409 position:21% line:83% align:start
Aquafaese are immune
to the mittsual.

00:49:02.443 --> 00:49:03.578 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hmm?

00:49:06.246 --> 00:49:07.682 position:41% line:89% align:start
Ohfan.

00:49:07.715 --> 00:49:09.450 position:30% line:89% align:start
(horse neighs)

00:49:12.386 --> 00:49:13.555 position:35% line:89% align:start
(straining)

00:49:13.588 --> 00:49:15.590 position:41% line:83% align:start
 <i>VOICE:</i>
 <i>Why do you fight?</i>

00:49:15.623 --> 00:49:17.659 position:38% line:89% align:start
 <i>Give in.</i>

00:49:18.760 --> 00:49:20.160 position:35% line:89% align:start
(grunting)

00:49:20.194 --> 00:49:21.361 position:41% line:83% align:start
-Dada!
-No!

00:49:21.395 --> 00:49:23.731 position:41% line:89% align:start
Dada...

00:49:25.232 --> 00:49:26.433 position:41% line:89% align:start
(gasps)

00:49:29.203 --> 00:49:31.238 position:35% line:89% align:start
(whooshing)

00:49:32.740 --> 00:49:34.642 position:24% line:83% align:start
(voice trembling):
Yuna.

00:49:40.380 --> 00:49:41.749 position:35% line:89% align:start
(screeches)

00:49:41.783 --> 00:49:44.017 position:38% line:89% align:start
(grunts)

00:49:44.051 --> 00:49:45.118 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yuna!

00:49:53.795 --> 00:49:56.063 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:49:56.096 --> 00:49:57.732 position:38% line:89% align:start
(gasping)

00:49:57.765 --> 00:49:59.634 position:33% line:89% align:start
Van, what...

00:49:59.667 --> 00:50:01.769 position:41% line:83% align:start
-Yuna!
-No!

00:50:01.803 --> 00:50:03.505 position:38% line:89% align:start
(panting)

00:50:03.538 --> 00:50:05.339 position:35% line:83% align:start
-(snarling)
-(gasps)

00:50:07.642 --> 00:50:08.743 position:41% line:83% align:start
 <i>VOICE:</i>
 <i>Zol.</i>

00:50:08.776 --> 00:50:11.278 position:30% line:89% align:start
(growls, barks)

00:50:22.256 --> 00:50:24.091 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:50:24.124 --> 00:50:25.593 position:41% line:89% align:start
Tohma!

00:50:25.627 --> 00:50:27.662 position:27% line:83% align:start
-Get this to Van.
-Right.

00:50:30.163 --> 00:50:31.666 position:38% line:89% align:start
(grunts)

00:50:31.699 --> 00:50:33.668 position:35% line:89% align:start
Go, Olaha!

00:50:37.839 --> 00:50:40.073 position:38% line:89% align:start
(panting)

00:50:41.843 --> 00:50:44.278 position:38% line:89% align:start
(grunts)

00:50:47.815 --> 00:50:50.484 position:10% line:83% align:start
-SOLDIER: What just happened?
-SOLDIER 2: Any casualties?

00:50:50.518 --> 00:50:53.153 position:19% line:83% align:start
SOLDIER 3: He went into
the forest. After him!

00:50:53.186 --> 00:50:55.455 position:35% line:83% align:start
SOLDIER 4:
Move, people. Get the horses!

00:50:56.423 --> 00:50:58.458 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:51:04.832 --> 00:51:06.834 position:35% line:89% align:start
(grunting)

00:51:12.472 --> 00:51:13.841 position:38% line:89% align:start
(grunts)

00:51:15.409 --> 00:51:17.612 position:44% line:83% align:start
 <i>VAN:</i>
 <i>Focus, Van.</i>

00:51:19.212 --> 00:51:20.848 position:33% line:89% align:start
 <i>Focus, Van.</i>

00:51:21.849 --> 00:51:23.618 position:35% line:89% align:start
 <i>I know...</i>

00:51:25.653 --> 00:51:27.622 position:35% line:89% align:start
 <i>I know...</i>

00:51:27.655 --> 00:51:29.189 position:35% line:89% align:start
 <i>who I am!</i>

00:51:29.222 --> 00:51:31.258 position:35% line:89% align:start
(straining)

00:51:36.698 --> 00:51:38.600 position:41% line:89% align:start
(yells)

00:51:39.601 --> 00:51:42.570 position:38% line:89% align:start
(barking)

00:51:46.774 --> 00:51:48.776 position:35% line:83% align:start
(groaning):
Yuna.

00:51:55.583 --> 00:51:57.217 position:38% line:89% align:start
(grunts)

00:51:58.185 --> 00:51:59.219 position:38% line:89% align:start
(groans)

00:52:02.489 --> 00:52:04.659 position:21% line:89% align:start
(Van panting gruffly)

00:52:15.770 --> 00:52:17.170 position:30% line:89% align:start
(yells in pain)

00:52:19.574 --> 00:52:21.542 position:35% line:89% align:start
(straining)

00:52:30.785 --> 00:52:32.319 position:38% line:89% align:start
Leave me.

00:52:38.793 --> 00:52:40.494 position:24% line:89% align:start
This is for Aquafa!

00:52:40.528 --> 00:52:41.796 position:38% line:89% align:start
(panting)

00:52:41.829 --> 00:52:43.296 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yuna.

00:52:51.906 --> 00:52:53.808 position:10% line:83% align:start
-HOHSALLE: Stop right there.
-SAE: Huh?

00:52:57.812 --> 00:52:59.547 position:27% line:89% align:start
(groaning softly)

00:53:00.581 --> 00:53:02.215 position:33% line:89% align:start
He said halt.

00:53:03.250 --> 00:53:04.886 position:35% line:89% align:start
Hey, stop!

00:53:04.919 --> 00:53:06.754 position:24% line:89% align:start
Didn't you hear me?

00:53:06.788 --> 00:53:08.723 position:24% line:89% align:start
Hey, wait! (groans)

00:53:13.427 --> 00:53:15.462 position:35% line:89% align:start
(groaning)

00:53:16.864 --> 00:53:18.900 position:19% line:89% align:start
No. Sir Hohsalle, stop!

00:53:18.933 --> 00:53:21.435 position:21% line:83% align:start
-Don't get too close.
-(Van wheezes)

00:53:25.606 --> 00:53:26.908 position:38% line:83% align:start
MAKOKAN:
Unbelievable.

00:53:26.941 --> 00:53:28.543 position:19% line:89% align:start
What's wrong with him?

00:53:28.576 --> 00:53:31.512 position:13% line:83% align:start
Makokan, lead Tohlim's men
away from here now.

00:53:31.546 --> 00:53:34.515 position:10% line:83% align:start
If we let them find this man,
they're going to kill him.

00:53:34.549 --> 00:53:35.850 position:38% line:89% align:start
Now, go!

00:53:35.883 --> 00:53:37.919 position:41% line:89% align:start
But...

00:53:37.952 --> 00:53:39.721 position:24% line:83% align:start
I don't understand
what's going on,

00:53:39.754 --> 00:53:41.689 position:21% line:89% align:start
but understood, sir.

00:53:41.723 --> 00:53:43.658 position:7% line:89% align:start
Do not take unnecessary risks.

00:53:43.691 --> 00:53:45.225 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hyah!

00:54:01.308 --> 00:54:03.343 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:54:05.312 --> 00:54:07.414 position:33% line:89% align:start
You're home.

00:54:07.447 --> 00:54:09.416 position:10% line:83% align:start
-So good to see you, my dear.
-(chuckling)

00:54:09.449 --> 00:54:11.786 position:38% line:89% align:start
(gasping)

00:54:14.789 --> 00:54:17.424 position:21% line:89% align:start
Why do you fight it?

00:54:17.457 --> 00:54:20.293 position:33% line:89% align:start
Just give in.

00:54:20.327 --> 00:54:22.496 position:24% line:89% align:start
Do you not feel it?

00:54:22.530 --> 00:54:24.665 position:21% line:89% align:start
The howl of the wind?

00:54:24.699 --> 00:54:27.668 position:13% line:89% align:start
The grass and the flowers?

00:54:27.702 --> 00:54:30.872 position:19% line:89% align:start
The birds, the beasts?

00:54:30.905 --> 00:54:33.674 position:7% line:89% align:start
You can feel all forms of life,

00:54:33.708 --> 00:54:37.310 position:24% line:83% align:start
because you are now
at one with them.

00:54:37.344 --> 00:54:40.047 position:24% line:89% align:start
That is Inside Out.

00:54:40.081 --> 00:54:41.883 position:35% line:89% align:start
Inside Out?

00:54:41.916 --> 00:54:46.053 position:19% line:83% align:start
Yes. That is the power
you possess.

00:54:46.087 --> 00:54:48.388 position:44% line:83% align:start
VAN:
Yuna!

00:54:48.421 --> 00:54:49.590 position:33% line:89% align:start
KENOI: Come.

00:54:49.624 --> 00:54:51.058 position:38% line:89% align:start
Find me.

00:54:51.092 --> 00:54:53.060 position:27% line:89% align:start
My name is Kenoi.

00:54:53.094 --> 00:54:54.829 position:41% line:89% align:start
(gasps)

00:54:57.098 --> 00:54:59.432 position:35% line:89% align:start
(groaning)

00:55:09.043 --> 00:55:11.712 position:21% line:83% align:start
Why would Tohlim try
to get rid of his blood?

00:55:13.714 --> 00:55:15.683 position:21% line:83% align:start
Clearly, he believes
the Aquafaese

00:55:15.716 --> 00:55:17.985 position:13% line:89% align:start
are immune to the mittsual.

00:55:18.019 --> 00:55:21.088 position:13% line:83% align:start
I suspect he has something
to do with the outbreak.

00:55:21.122 --> 00:55:23.925 position:13% line:83% align:start
It's exactly what happened
80 years ago.

00:55:23.958 --> 00:55:25.993 position:16% line:83% align:start
The mittsual's being used
against Zol

00:55:26.027 --> 00:55:28.696 position:19% line:83% align:start
in the hopes of gaining
Aquafa's independence.

00:55:29.697 --> 00:55:33.601 position:10% line:83% align:start
But there is no guarantee it
will remain an ally to Aquafa.

00:55:34.969 --> 00:55:38.005 position:21% line:83% align:start
SAE: My entire family
was murdered by Zolians.

00:55:38.039 --> 00:55:40.508 position:21% line:83% align:start
The black wolf fever
is retribution.

00:55:40.541 --> 00:55:43.010 position:5% line:89% align:start
So taking his life is justified?

00:55:46.013 --> 00:55:47.982 position:21% line:89% align:start
(Van groaning softly)

00:55:51.018 --> 00:55:53.521 position:33% line:83% align:start
-Stand down.
-(scoffs)

00:55:53.554 --> 00:55:55.857 position:24% line:83% align:start
Stop. You shouldn't
be moving around.

00:55:57.758 --> 00:56:00.528 position:35% line:89% align:start
(groaning)

00:56:02.495 --> 00:56:06.701 position:13% line:83% align:start
Do you see? Your wounds are
far too serious for that.

00:56:06.734 --> 00:56:08.102 position:27% line:89% align:start
Lie down for now.

00:56:08.135 --> 00:56:09.971 position:7% line:89% align:start
You can trust me. I'm a doctor.

00:56:10.004 --> 00:56:12.106 position:10% line:89% align:start
Just forget about that woman.

00:56:14.642 --> 00:56:17.645 position:7% line:89% align:start
Hey, listen. We need you alive.

00:56:18.846 --> 00:56:20.615 position:24% line:89% align:start
I should thank you.

00:56:20.648 --> 00:56:22.783 position:30% line:83% align:start
These bandages
may have saved my life.

00:56:22.817 --> 00:56:24.417 position:27% line:89% align:start
Do not thank me.

00:56:24.451 --> 00:56:27.454 position:30% line:83% align:start
I am only here
because I need your blood.

00:56:27.487 --> 00:56:30.057 position:10% line:89% align:start
Sorry, but I made a promise.

00:56:30.091 --> 00:56:32.560 position:21% line:89% align:start
Hey, wait! (whimpers)

00:56:32.593 --> 00:56:34.996 position:21% line:89% align:start
I have to find Yuna.

00:56:39.499 --> 00:56:41.168 position:38% line:89% align:start
(grunts)

00:56:43.470 --> 00:56:45.506 position:10% line:89% align:start
My name is Hohsalle Yuguraul.

00:56:45.539 --> 00:56:47.474 position:19% line:89% align:start
I propose an exchange.

00:56:47.508 --> 00:56:49.510 position:13% line:89% align:start
Allow me to accompany you.

00:56:49.543 --> 00:56:52.046 position:30% line:83% align:start
Along the way,
I will tend to your wounds.

00:56:52.079 --> 00:56:54.949 position:16% line:83% align:start
Because you have lost far
too much precious blood already.

00:56:55.983 --> 00:56:58.152 position:38% line:83% align:start
However,
you'll let me take some of it

00:56:58.185 --> 00:57:00.453 position:21% line:83% align:start
once you've recovered
and the journey is done.

00:57:00.487 --> 00:57:01.589 position:44% line:89% align:start
Fair?

00:57:01.622 --> 00:57:02.890 position:24% line:89% align:start
Hey, tracker woman!

00:57:02.924 --> 00:57:04.959 position:7% line:89% align:start
We'll need your help, as well.

00:57:04.992 --> 00:57:07.460 position:21% line:83% align:start
We must find someone
called Yuna.

00:57:07.494 --> 00:57:09.130 position:30% line:89% align:start
All is settled.

00:57:09.163 --> 00:57:11.464 position:13% line:83% align:start
Get down from there so that
I can redress your wounds.

00:57:11.498 --> 00:57:13.534 position:27% line:89% align:start
Come along, Van.

00:57:16.837 --> 00:57:19.507 position:10% line:83% align:start
While we're at it, I'll take
a look at your shoulder.

00:57:21.809 --> 00:57:23.911 position:30% line:89% align:start
(birds calling)

00:57:23.945 --> 00:57:26.113 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:57:33.854 --> 00:57:38.092 position:35% line:77% align:start
 <i>HOHSALLE:</i>
 <i>And so, I came to travel with</i>
 <i>the man who holds the key.</i>

00:57:38.125 --> 00:57:40.227 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>Strange as it may seem,</i>

00:57:40.261 --> 00:57:42.563 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>the woman who once</i>
 <i>wanted his head</i>

00:57:42.596 --> 00:57:45.132 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>became the navigator</i>
 <i>for our journey.</i>

00:57:48.069 --> 00:57:50.104 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:58:02.750 --> 00:58:04.251 position:19% line:89% align:start
Perhaps we should rest.

00:58:04.285 --> 00:58:06.554 position:24% line:83% align:start
Not until we reach
the next forest.

00:58:06.587 --> 00:58:09.489 position:24% line:83% align:start
This area is prone
to avalanches.

00:58:14.195 --> 00:58:15.730 position:38% line:83% align:start
HOHSALLE:
Amazing.

00:58:15.763 --> 00:58:18.799 position:30% line:83% align:start
His wounds have
completely healed.

00:58:18.833 --> 00:58:20.868 position:44% line:83% align:start
SAE:
I'll go hunt for food.

00:58:20.901 --> 00:58:23.671 position:13% line:83% align:start
-You find us some firewood.
-(gasps) You mean me?

00:58:32.646 --> 00:58:35.149 position:44% line:83% align:start
VAN:
Those won't work.

00:58:35.182 --> 00:58:38.552 position:21% line:83% align:start
That wood's too damp.
It's not gonna burn.

00:58:38.586 --> 00:58:40.755 position:16% line:83% align:start
You're better off taking
branches from the trees.

00:58:40.788 --> 00:58:42.523 position:16% line:89% align:start
(wood clatters on ground)

00:58:46.927 --> 00:58:47.862 position:41% line:89% align:start
(sighs)

00:58:47.895 --> 00:58:50.264 position:24% line:83% align:start
Will this wood burn
bright enough, master?

00:58:53.334 --> 00:58:55.202 position:13% line:89% align:start
You said you want my blood.

00:58:56.637 --> 00:58:59.040 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Yes.
-What for?

00:59:00.241 --> 00:59:02.777 position:35% line:83% align:start
 <i>HOHSALLE:</i>
 <i>Well...</i>

00:59:02.810 --> 00:59:07.181 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>this land is plagued by</i>
 <i>a disease called the mittsual.</i>

00:59:07.214 --> 00:59:10.184 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>It's spread by ossam dogs.</i>

00:59:10.217 --> 00:59:13.721 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>You were bitten by one</i>
 <i>in the salt mine, right?</i>

00:59:13.754 --> 00:59:16.924 position:27% line:83% align:start
But you survived
and didn't get sick.

00:59:16.957 --> 00:59:20.227 position:16% line:83% align:start
And that means your blood
could provide us with a cure.

00:59:20.261 --> 00:59:22.930 position:30% line:83% align:start
It can do that?
But it's only my blood.

00:59:24.165 --> 00:59:26.600 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>HOHSALLE: Think of snakebites,</i>
 <i>for example.</i>

00:59:26.634 --> 00:59:28.235 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>To treat those,</i>
 <i>we dilute the blood</i>

00:59:28.269 --> 00:59:30.004 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>of someone who was poisoned</i>

00:59:30.037 --> 00:59:33.040 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>and transfuse it</i>
 <i>into the patient.</i>

00:59:33.074 --> 00:59:34.809 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>Because that infected blood</i>
 <i>remembers</i>

00:59:34.842 --> 00:59:36.377 position:33% line:83% align:start
 <i>how to fight</i>
 <i>against the poison,</i>

00:59:36.410 --> 00:59:39.680 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>it weakens the effects</i>
 <i>of the snakebite.</i>

00:59:41.816 --> 00:59:43.818 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>It's the same here.</i>

00:59:43.851 --> 00:59:47.254 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>Your blood was able</i>
 <i>to defeat the mittsual.</i>

00:59:48.289 --> 00:59:51.892 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>And that makes it a very</i>
 <i>powerful weapon in this fight.</i>

00:59:54.261 --> 00:59:56.230 position:21% line:83% align:start
I would like to wield
that weapon

00:59:56.263 --> 00:59:58.899 position:10% line:89% align:start
so we can defeat the disease.

00:59:58.933 --> 01:00:01.836 position:10% line:89% align:start
You're right. I did survive.

01:00:01.869 --> 01:00:04.805 position:10% line:89% align:start
But no, I did not defeat it.

01:00:04.839 --> 01:00:08.075 position:13% line:83% align:start
The disease still lives on
inside of me.

01:00:08.109 --> 01:00:10.277 position:27% line:83% align:start
And it might even
be more than that.

01:00:10.311 --> 01:00:13.047 position:13% line:83% align:start
For all I know, the disease
is keeping me alive.

01:00:14.148 --> 01:00:15.749 position:41% line:89% align:start
(gasps)

01:00:24.125 --> 01:00:26.160 position:35% line:83% align:start
 <i>HOHSALLE:</i>
 <i>"Keeping me alive."</i>

01:00:27.128 --> 01:00:30.097 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>What an odd thing to say.</i>

01:00:30.131 --> 01:00:33.167 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>I've seen so many die</i>
 <i>because of the mittsual.</i>

01:00:34.401 --> 01:00:37.104 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>Inside of this man,</i>

01:00:37.138 --> 01:00:39.907 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>I wonder what face it's chosen</i>
 <i>to wear now.</i>

01:00:41.142 --> 01:00:45.412 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>Whatever it is,</i>
 <i>I'd like to see it for myself.</i>

01:00:47.381 --> 01:00:49.350 position:35% line:89% align:start
Say, Van...

01:00:49.383 --> 01:00:51.752 position:21% line:83% align:start
who is this Yuna that
you're risking your life for?

01:00:51.785 --> 01:00:53.154 position:35% line:89% align:start
Your wife?

01:00:53.187 --> 01:00:55.890 position:13% line:83% align:start
An epidemic killed my wife
a long time ago.

01:00:55.923 --> 01:00:57.958 position:27% line:89% align:start
My son, as well.

01:00:57.992 --> 01:00:59.927 position:16% line:89% align:start
I see. Then who is Yuna?

01:01:01.195 --> 01:01:02.930 position:33% line:89% align:start
My daughter.

01:01:09.270 --> 01:01:11.805 position:35% line:89% align:start
(neighing)

01:01:24.818 --> 01:01:28.355 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>HOHSALLE: His injuries healed</i>
 <i>remarkably fast.</i>

01:01:28.389 --> 01:01:30.925 position:33% line:83% align:start
 <i>The strength</i>
 <i>of the Lone Antler?</i>

01:01:30.958 --> 01:01:33.961 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>Or perhaps it was</i>
 <i>because of the mittsual.</i>

01:01:34.962 --> 01:01:39.066 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>I'm a sacred doctor,</i>
 <i>vaunted throughout the land,</i>

01:01:39.099 --> 01:01:42.203 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>and yet I'm eating</i>
 <i>parasite-infested meat.</i>

01:01:45.507 --> 01:01:47.474 position:44% line:83% align:start
VAN:
Can I borrow that?

01:02:03.257 --> 01:02:05.859 position:24% line:89% align:start
(insects chirping)

01:02:18.973 --> 01:02:20.841 position:44% line:83% align:start
 <i>VAN:</i>
 <i>My daughter.</i>

01:02:38.225 --> 01:02:40.261 position:35% line:89% align:start
(rumbling)

01:02:43.364 --> 01:02:44.765 position:41% line:89% align:start
(gasps)

01:02:49.537 --> 01:02:51.105 position:33% line:89% align:start
Where is he?

01:02:51.138 --> 01:02:52.574 position:33% line:89% align:start
Where's Van?

01:02:52.607 --> 01:02:54.842 position:16% line:89% align:start
He's feeding his pyuika.

01:03:06.920 --> 01:03:09.056 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>KENOI: Humans do not possess</i>
 <i>the ability</i>

01:03:09.089 --> 01:03:11.158 position:30% line:83% align:start
 <i>to see within</i>
 <i>their own bodies.</i>

01:03:11.191 --> 01:03:14.828 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>But now you are Inside Out,</i>
 <i>so you have gained awareness.</i>

01:03:14.862 --> 01:03:17.364 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>Souls and bodies are separate</i>
 <i>from one another.</i>

01:03:17.398 --> 01:03:19.867 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>All living creatures</i>
 <i>in this world are one.</i>

01:03:19.900 --> 01:03:21.935 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>Your body is merely a vessel,</i>

01:03:21.969 --> 01:03:24.071 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>acting as an anchor</i>
 <i>for your soul.</i>

01:03:24.104 --> 01:03:27.074 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>You were bitten.</i>
 <i>Now what do you see?</i>

01:03:27.107 --> 01:03:29.443 position:27% line:83% align:start
(Kenoi's voice):
Do not fear the light.

01:03:29.476 --> 01:03:32.279 position:16% line:89% align:start
Because you are now free.

01:03:32.313 --> 01:03:34.081 position:41% line:89% align:start
(gasps)

01:03:36.483 --> 01:03:38.452 position:5% line:89% align:start
What's wrong? Are you all right?

01:03:38.485 --> 01:03:40.321 position:19% line:89% align:start
Are your wounds aching?

01:03:40.354 --> 01:03:42.189 position:47% line:89% align:start
No.

01:03:42.222 --> 01:03:45.392 position:7% line:83% align:start
Sometimes I can hear the voice
of the man who took Yuna.

01:03:45.426 --> 01:03:46.960 position:38% line:89% align:start
It's odd.

01:03:46.994 --> 01:03:49.196 position:10% line:89% align:start
I find it reassuring somehow.

01:03:49.229 --> 01:03:51.065 position:19% line:89% align:start
And that frightens me.

01:03:55.369 --> 01:03:56.904 position:35% line:89% align:start
Come along.

01:03:56.937 --> 01:03:59.273 position:19% line:89% align:start
Yuna's waiting for you.

01:03:59.306 --> 01:04:00.941 position:41% line:89% align:start
Right.

01:04:01.909 --> 01:04:03.944 position:30% line:89% align:start
(birds calling)

01:04:09.116 --> 01:04:11.085 position:44% line:83% align:start
SAE:
I'd be careful out here.

01:04:11.118 --> 01:04:12.486 position:30% line:83% align:start
This far west,
the people still have

01:04:12.520 --> 01:04:15.089 position:10% line:89% align:start
a deep-seated hatred for Zol.

01:04:15.122 --> 01:04:16.323 position:35% line:89% align:start
We will be.

01:04:16.357 --> 01:04:18.092 position:30% line:83% align:start
Does that mean
you hail from the west?

01:04:24.465 --> 01:04:27.234 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

01:04:27.267 --> 01:04:29.236 position:38% line:83% align:start
 <i>OFFICER:</i>
 <i>Are you sure, my lord?</i>

01:04:29.269 --> 01:04:32.172 position:5% line:83% align:start
Should you not be there to greet
His Majesty the Emperor?

01:04:32.206 --> 01:04:34.074 position:47% line:89% align:start
No.

01:04:34.108 --> 01:04:36.377 position:30% line:83% align:start
The emperor has
no interest in me anymore.

01:04:36.410 --> 01:04:40.114 position:16% line:83% align:start
Come. An imperial prince
still has other duties.

01:04:43.951 --> 01:04:45.452 position:33% line:83% align:start
AQUAFA KING:
They've issued a decree

01:04:45.486 --> 01:04:48.255 position:21% line:83% align:start
for our army to join
their military campaign?

01:04:48.288 --> 01:04:51.492 position:19% line:83% align:start
And they've reminded us
we must prevent rebellion,

01:04:51.526 --> 01:04:53.927 position:10% line:89% align:start
per the terms of our treaty.

01:04:53.961 --> 01:04:55.462 position:24% line:89% align:start
Of course they did.

01:04:55.496 --> 01:04:57.331 position:16% line:89% align:start
So remind me, who told me

01:04:57.364 --> 01:05:00.067 position:21% line:83% align:start
Yotalu would make Zol
easier to control?

01:05:00.100 --> 01:05:02.469 position:19% line:89% align:start
My apologies, Highness.

01:05:02.503 --> 01:05:04.539 position:24% line:83% align:start
And what would you
have us do now?

01:05:04.572 --> 01:05:06.407 position:16% line:89% align:start
We must obey the decree.

01:05:06.440 --> 01:05:08.242 position:10% line:89% align:start
It's the only choice we have

01:05:08.275 --> 01:05:11.278 position:21% line:83% align:start
to avoid falling foul
of the emperor.

01:05:11.311 --> 01:05:12.614 position:35% line:89% align:start
Wonderful.

01:05:12.647 --> 01:05:15.382 position:13% line:89% align:start
How did this happen to us?

01:05:15.416 --> 01:05:18.018 position:16% line:83% align:start
I've no excuse to offer,
Your Highness.

01:05:18.051 --> 01:05:19.953 position:16% line:83% align:start
But if we have patience,
we can afford

01:05:19.987 --> 01:05:22.423 position:13% line:89% align:start
to lose Fire Horse Village.

01:05:22.456 --> 01:05:24.425 position:21% line:83% align:start
As long as the ossam
are still alive,

01:05:24.458 --> 01:05:27.027 position:16% line:89% align:start
we will succeed one day.

01:05:27.060 --> 01:05:29.697 position:21% line:83% align:start
You dare speak to me
of patience?

01:05:29.731 --> 01:05:31.365 position:27% line:89% align:start
For our country,

01:05:31.398 --> 01:05:33.434 position:7% line:89% align:start
in the interest of its future.

01:05:34.468 --> 01:05:36.671 position:21% line:89% align:start
What about Hohsalle?

01:05:36.704 --> 01:05:39.373 position:10% line:89% align:start
If he manages to find a cure,

01:05:39.406 --> 01:05:42.610 position:19% line:83% align:start
that future we dream of
shall never come.

01:05:43.477 --> 01:05:45.513 position:19% line:83% align:start
The key to all of that
is the man

01:05:45.547 --> 01:05:47.948 position:7% line:89% align:start
who escaped from the salt mine.

01:05:49.617 --> 01:05:53.655 position:21% line:83% align:start
All we have to do is
remove him from the equation.

01:05:59.226 --> 01:06:01.995 position:16% line:83% align:start
ELDER: The anger of some
has been reignited

01:06:02.029 --> 01:06:04.231 position:33% line:83% align:start
by the return
of the Emperor's Eyes.

01:06:04.264 --> 01:06:07.267 position:16% line:83% align:start
And all the rumors about
the mittsual coming back again

01:06:07.301 --> 01:06:09.269 position:10% line:89% align:start
are only fanning the flames.

01:06:09.303 --> 01:06:11.739 position:16% line:83% align:start
This land used to belong
to Aquafa.

01:06:11.773 --> 01:06:14.208 position:16% line:89% align:start
This is Zol's punishment.

01:06:14.241 --> 01:06:16.210 position:41% line:83% align:start
ELDER:
The lord and his wife cared

01:06:16.243 --> 01:06:18.145 position:10% line:83% align:start
for the people of our village
a great deal,

01:06:18.178 --> 01:06:20.247 position:10% line:89% align:start
and they were good and kind.

01:06:20.280 --> 01:06:22.382 position:21% line:83% align:start
They were the reason
our village was able

01:06:22.416 --> 01:06:24.318 position:10% line:89% align:start
to prosper as much as it did.

01:06:24.351 --> 01:06:25.687 position:33% line:89% align:start
Foolishness.

01:06:25.720 --> 01:06:27.755 position:27% line:83% align:start
Sir, do you know
where my mother went?

01:06:27.789 --> 01:06:29.089 position:41% line:89% align:start
(gasps)

01:06:29.122 --> 01:06:31.024 position:30% line:89% align:start
(fire rumbling)

01:06:35.630 --> 01:06:38.098 position:41% line:83% align:start
ELDER:
An Aquafaese curse.

01:06:38.131 --> 01:06:40.367 position:30% line:83% align:start
There are many
who call the mittsual

01:06:40.400 --> 01:06:43.136 position:16% line:89% align:start
Zol's divine punishment.

01:06:43.170 --> 01:06:44.539 position:38% line:89% align:start
Let's go.

01:06:49.243 --> 01:06:51.445 position:27% line:83% align:start
I only pray that
this doesn't lead

01:06:51.478 --> 01:06:54.047 position:10% line:89% align:start
to another war breaking out.

01:06:59.787 --> 01:07:03.223 position:27% line:83% align:start
Why was I the one
to survive this disease?

01:07:11.699 --> 01:07:14.234 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

01:07:14.268 --> 01:07:15.770 position:35% line:83% align:start
 <i>HOHSALLE:</i>
 <i>The mittsual.</i>

01:07:15.803 --> 01:07:18.606 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>It kills Zolians</i>
 <i>but not Aquafaese.</i>

01:07:18.640 --> 01:07:20.440 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>There has to be a reason.</i>

01:07:21.676 --> 01:07:24.144 position:19% line:89% align:start
 <i>It is not mere chance.</i>

01:07:24.177 --> 01:07:26.280 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>If we look closely,</i>
 <i>we will find</i>

01:07:26.313 --> 01:07:29.416 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>the hidden threads</i>
 <i>of the true cause.</i>

01:07:29.449 --> 01:07:33.320 position:27% line:77% align:start
 <i>And by following</i>
 <i>those threads,</i>
 <i>we will save many lives.</i>

01:07:35.122 --> 01:07:38.492 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>Trusting that is the basis</i>
 <i>of the medical arts.</i>

01:07:38.526 --> 01:07:40.528 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

01:07:45.432 --> 01:07:47.200 position:38% line:83% align:start
HOHSALLE:
Van.

01:07:47.234 --> 01:07:49.704 position:19% line:83% align:start
There must be a reason
why you survived.

01:07:49.737 --> 01:07:52.205 position:10% line:89% align:start
We just haven't found it yet.

01:07:54.809 --> 01:07:57.144 position:44% line:83% align:start
VAN:
These medical arts of yours,

01:07:57.177 --> 01:07:59.112 position:13% line:89% align:start
do they just save the body?

01:07:59.146 --> 01:08:00.380 position:27% line:89% align:start
Or the soul, too?

01:08:00.414 --> 01:08:03.483 position:10% line:83% align:start
As long as the body is saved,
the soul will be saved, as well.

01:08:03.518 --> 01:08:05.853 position:24% line:89% align:start
Yuna saved my soul.

01:08:05.887 --> 01:08:08.255 position:16% line:89% align:start
Without her, I'd be lost.

01:08:12.860 --> 01:08:14.829 position:35% line:83% align:start
 <i>HOHSALLE:</i>
 <i>His soul.</i>

01:08:14.862 --> 01:08:17.699 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>The way he speaks of it,</i>

01:08:17.732 --> 01:08:20.300 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>it sounds different somehow,</i>

01:08:20.334 --> 01:08:23.503 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>compared to the soul</i>
 <i>the priest-doctors believe in.</i>

01:08:31.512 --> 01:08:33.514 position:27% line:89% align:start
(horse whinnies)

01:08:38.452 --> 01:08:40.253 position:35% line:89% align:start
(rumbling)

01:08:48.663 --> 01:08:50.765 position:27% line:83% align:start
-(horse neighing)
-Whoa.

01:08:53.233 --> 01:08:55.202 position:27% line:83% align:start
It's a guide for
the emperor's balloon.

01:08:55.235 --> 01:08:56.771 position:21% line:89% align:start
He's getting closer.

01:08:58.405 --> 01:09:00.240 position:38% line:83% align:start
HOHSALLE:
The Emperor's Eyes visit.

01:09:01.676 --> 01:09:03.678 position:19% line:89% align:start
Then we must be close.

01:09:04.712 --> 01:09:08.516 position:10% line:83% align:start
Yes. Fire Horse Village isn't
much farther from here.

01:09:09.717 --> 01:09:13.253 position:38% line:77% align:start
HOHSALLE:
This place was once protected
by the mittsual.

01:09:13.286 --> 01:09:15.489 position:13% line:89% align:start
Yet another hidden thread.

01:09:15.523 --> 01:09:17.792 position:24% line:89% align:start
(distant rumbling)

01:09:17.825 --> 01:09:19.827 position:35% line:89% align:start
(snarling)

01:09:28.836 --> 01:09:31.438 position:21% line:83% align:start
I can no longer hear
the sound of any voices.

01:09:31.471 --> 01:09:32.607 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh.

01:09:32.640 --> 01:09:35.442 position:30% line:89% align:start
(child crying)

01:09:45.586 --> 01:09:49.289 position:10% line:83% align:start
The young ones let themselves
get bitten again?

01:09:49.322 --> 01:09:50.758 position:38% line:89% align:start
Yes, sir.

01:09:50.792 --> 01:09:53.728 position:19% line:83% align:start
They seem to have snuck
into the sanctuary at night.

01:09:56.664 --> 01:09:58.566 position:41% line:83% align:start
OHFAN:
They should have known better.

01:09:58.599 --> 01:10:00.835 position:27% line:83% align:start
They're incapable
of receiving the power.

01:10:01.869 --> 01:10:04.906 position:27% line:83% align:start
Chief Ohfan,
they only wished to repay you.

01:10:04.939 --> 01:10:06.473 position:35% line:89% align:start
The fools.

01:10:07.975 --> 01:10:10.845 position:19% line:83% align:start
They wished to succeed
their king.

01:10:14.347 --> 01:10:16.383 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

01:10:29.897 --> 01:10:31.899 position:13% line:83% align:start
-SAE: Dismount your horses.
-HOHSALLE: Hmm?

01:10:41.308 --> 01:10:43.644 position:24% line:83% align:start
-(Hohsalle grunts)
-(horse neighing)

01:10:49.817 --> 01:10:51.552 position:33% line:89% align:start
Stilt-walker.

01:10:54.589 --> 01:10:55.923 position:24% line:89% align:start
High on your left.

01:10:59.927 --> 01:11:01.394 position:38% line:89% align:start
(grunts)

01:11:22.650 --> 01:11:24.752 position:41% line:89% align:start
(gasps)

01:11:35.096 --> 01:11:37.565 position:21% line:89% align:start
(stilt-walker grunts)

01:11:38.566 --> 01:11:40.835 position:16% line:83% align:start
What are you doing?
We are Aquafaese, too.

01:11:40.868 --> 01:11:42.904 position:30% line:89% align:start
Why attack us?

01:11:56.584 --> 01:11:59.687 position:21% line:83% align:start
We can all be blinded
by our fear and hatred.

01:12:00.755 --> 01:12:02.790 position:13% line:89% align:start
I was once just like them.

01:12:07.028 --> 01:12:09.730 position:16% line:83% align:start
YOTALU: A few years ago,
I actually had an encounter

01:12:09.764 --> 01:12:12.365 position:19% line:89% align:start
with Broken Antler Van.

01:12:12.399 --> 01:12:14.869 position:7% line:89% align:start
Six Lone Antlers decimated us.

01:12:14.902 --> 01:12:17.004 position:35% line:83% align:start
My squadron
was almost wiped out.

01:12:17.038 --> 01:12:19.006 position:24% line:89% align:start
Lucky you survived.

01:12:19.040 --> 01:12:22.877 position:21% line:83% align:start
No, I was only a boy,
so Van refused to kill me.

01:12:22.910 --> 01:12:24.946 position:35% line:83% align:start
-(rumbling)
-(all gasp)

01:12:29.416 --> 01:12:31.619 position:10% line:89% align:start
(soldiers gasping, murmuring)

01:12:45.099 --> 01:12:48.769 position:41% line:83% align:start
(sighs)
Sorry to make us rest here.

01:12:48.803 --> 01:12:51.772 position:13% line:89% align:start
Not befitting of a doctor.

01:12:53.708 --> 01:12:57.745 position:13% line:89% align:start
Van, may I ask a question?

01:12:57.778 --> 01:13:01.048 position:27% line:83% align:start
What is she like,
this Yuna of yours?

01:13:04.451 --> 01:13:06.954 position:10% line:89% align:start
Where do I start? Yuna is...

01:13:06.988 --> 01:13:09.023 position:21% line:89% align:start
She has small hands.

01:13:09.056 --> 01:13:11.626 position:33% line:83% align:start
They're soft
and also a bit clingy.

01:13:11.659 --> 01:13:13.094 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

01:13:13.127 --> 01:13:16.097 position:21% line:83% align:start
Her cheeks are rosy,
round and warm.

01:13:16.130 --> 01:13:18.833 position:10% line:83% align:start
Her hair is a little unruly,
but...

01:13:18.866 --> 01:13:22.069 position:19% line:83% align:start
tying it into pigtails
makes her smile with delight.

01:13:23.537 --> 01:13:25.438 position:24% line:89% align:start
She loves to smile.

01:13:25.472 --> 01:13:27.608 position:24% line:89% align:start
She likes animals.

01:13:27.642 --> 01:13:30.511 position:16% line:89% align:start
But insects, not so much.

01:13:30.544 --> 01:13:33.446 position:7% line:89% align:start
She loves to drink pyuika milk.

01:13:33.480 --> 01:13:36.517 position:27% line:83% align:start
And she knows how
to milk them herself, too.

01:13:36.550 --> 01:13:39.452 position:24% line:83% align:start
Meat tastes better
when I'm around her.

01:13:39.486 --> 01:13:41.789 position:19% line:83% align:start
She can't chew her food
very well,

01:13:41.822 --> 01:13:44.525 position:30% line:83% align:start
but she smiles
when she's got a mouthful.

01:13:44.558 --> 01:13:48.461 position:7% line:83% align:start
Sometimes when she's sleeping,
she'll latch onto my back.

01:13:48.495 --> 01:13:49.964 position:27% line:89% align:start
(chuckles softly)

01:13:49.997 --> 01:13:52.667 position:27% line:83% align:start
Holds on so tight
it hurts a little bit.

01:13:53.801 --> 01:13:57.004 position:13% line:83% align:start
I can't say I ever dreamed
of being a father again,

01:13:57.038 --> 01:14:00.141 position:21% line:83% align:start
but all I want to do
is show her everything.

01:14:00.174 --> 01:14:02.076 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>I want to see her grow,</i>

01:14:02.109 --> 01:14:05.112 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>to fall in love with someone,</i>
 <i>get married, and...</i>

01:14:05.146 --> 01:14:08.849 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>I want to keep watching</i>
 <i>over her all the while.</i>

01:14:13.521 --> 01:14:15.523 position:44% line:83% align:start
SAE:
A deer whistle?

01:14:17.658 --> 01:14:18.993 position:44% line:83% align:start
VAN:
Yes.

01:14:20.728 --> 01:14:23.597 position:16% line:83% align:start
The child you made it for
isn't really yours, though.

01:14:27.868 --> 01:14:29.570 position:27% line:89% align:start
Thanks for this.

01:14:31.839 --> 01:14:35.042 position:13% line:83% align:start
The child, she's an orphan
from a nearby village,

01:14:35.076 --> 01:14:38.245 position:7% line:83% align:start
given to an unstable salt miner
to calm her down.

01:14:38.279 --> 01:14:40.247 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yes.

01:14:40.281 --> 01:14:43.217 position:21% line:83% align:start
But there are things
more important than blood.

01:14:43.250 --> 01:14:45.219 position:21% line:89% align:start
Yuna is my daughter.

01:14:45.252 --> 01:14:47.722 position:16% line:83% align:start
-That's all that matters.
-(chuckles softly)

01:14:47.755 --> 01:14:49.523 position:13% line:89% align:start
The way you talk reminds me

01:14:49.557 --> 01:14:51.726 position:7% line:83% align:start
that some things are invisible
to a tracker.

01:14:51.759 --> 01:14:54.795 position:7% line:83% align:start
You'll want to travel northwest
from these hot springs.

01:14:54.829 --> 01:14:57.064 position:27% line:83% align:start
Follow the valley
when you reach it.

01:14:57.098 --> 01:14:59.667 position:24% line:83% align:start
That will lead you
to Fire Horse Village.

01:14:59.700 --> 01:15:02.003 position:27% line:83% align:start
The ossam will be
waiting for you.

01:15:02.036 --> 01:15:03.771 position:10% line:89% align:start
Your daughter will be there.

01:15:04.872 --> 01:15:08.309 position:10% line:83% align:start
Why did you go to the trouble
of bringing us out this far?

01:15:08.342 --> 01:15:11.579 position:21% line:83% align:start
SAE: She's a survivor
of the mittsual, too.

01:15:13.581 --> 01:15:16.183 position:16% line:83% align:start
I was planning on killing
the both of you.

01:15:18.252 --> 01:15:20.888 position:27% line:89% align:start
Are you leaving?

01:15:20.921 --> 01:15:22.757 position:24% line:83% align:start
You found yourself
a good village.

01:15:22.790 --> 01:15:25.893 position:5% line:89% align:start
Take her back when you find her.

01:15:25.926 --> 01:15:28.162 position:13% line:89% align:start
My name's Sae, by the way.

01:15:28.195 --> 01:15:31.198 position:24% line:83% align:start
Next time we meet,
you can call me that.

01:15:35.770 --> 01:15:37.938 position:30% line:89% align:start
(grunts softly)

01:15:56.090 --> 01:15:58.092 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

01:16:01.362 --> 01:16:02.797 position:30% line:89% align:start
(gasps softly)

01:16:11.806 --> 01:16:13.174 position:41% line:89% align:start
(gasps)

01:16:17.978 --> 01:16:21.615 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>HOHSALLE: When I awoke,</i>
 <i>the woman had left us.</i>

01:16:21.649 --> 01:16:24.318 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>Van said I didn't need</i>
 <i>to follow him any further,</i>

01:16:24.351 --> 01:16:27.021 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>but I still needed</i>
 <i>some of his blood.</i>

01:16:28.322 --> 01:16:30.825 position:19% line:89% align:start
 <i>What was that, though?</i>

01:16:30.858 --> 01:16:32.960 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>What did I see that night?</i>

01:16:33.994 --> 01:16:35.796 position:33% line:89% align:start
I'm curious.

01:16:35.830 --> 01:16:38.732 position:19% line:83% align:start
That whistle you made--
I'd like to hear it.

01:16:41.402 --> 01:16:43.904 position:21% line:89% align:start
(whistle screeching)

01:16:43.938 --> 01:16:46.874 position:27% line:89% align:start
(whistle echoes)

01:16:52.880 --> 01:16:54.115 position:24% line:89% align:start
(Hohsalle chuckles)

01:16:54.148 --> 01:16:56.383 position:35% line:83% align:start
Not really
a pleasant sound, is it?

01:16:57.451 --> 01:16:59.286 position:33% line:89% align:start
(both laugh)

01:17:07.428 --> 01:17:10.064 position:7% line:89% align:start
Yuna's just beyond this tunnel.

01:17:10.097 --> 01:17:12.633 position:7% line:89% align:start
Yes. The land of the mittsual.

01:17:18.339 --> 01:17:21.075 position:16% line:89% align:start
Wha... Hey. Wait for me!

01:17:29.049 --> 01:17:31.852 position:41% line:83% align:start
 <i>KENOI:</i>
 <i>At last, you have come, Van.</i>

01:17:31.886 --> 01:17:34.054 position:24% line:89% align:start
 <i>I've been waiting.</i>

01:17:39.994 --> 01:17:42.196 position:24% line:89% align:start
(muffled grunting)

01:17:44.198 --> 01:17:47.168 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>KENOI: With your power,</i>
 <i>you will become one</i>

01:17:47.201 --> 01:17:50.004 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>with the village's</i>
 <i>remaining ossam.</i>

01:17:50.037 --> 01:17:53.908 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>They are the key</i>
 <i>to our future.</i>

01:17:53.941 --> 01:17:55.476 position:35% line:89% align:start
 <i>Come, Van.</i>

01:17:55.510 --> 01:17:58.212 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>Take your place as king.</i>

01:18:01.348 --> 01:18:03.350 position:27% line:89% align:start
(birds chirping)

01:18:12.793 --> 01:18:15.062 position:27% line:89% align:start
(horse whinnying)

01:18:15.095 --> 01:18:16.730 position:41% line:83% align:start
OHFAN:
You can rest easy.

01:18:16.764 --> 01:18:20.067 position:24% line:83% align:start
I promise to treat
the doctor as my guest.

01:18:22.770 --> 01:18:25.507 position:19% line:83% align:start
I was starting to worry
you wouldn't make it,

01:18:25.540 --> 01:18:29.443 position:24% line:83% align:start
Broken Antler Van,
leader of the Lone Antlers.

01:18:29.476 --> 01:18:34.381 position:19% line:83% align:start
You can call me Ohfan,
the chief of Fire Horse Village.

01:18:35.416 --> 01:18:37.251 position:19% line:89% align:start
Tell me where Yuna is.

01:18:39.119 --> 01:18:40.955 position:33% line:89% align:start
Come with me.

01:18:43.490 --> 01:18:45.492 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

01:19:00.007 --> 01:19:02.309 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

01:19:15.489 --> 01:19:17.458 position:33% line:89% align:start
Chief Ohfan.

01:19:17.491 --> 01:19:20.327 position:21% line:83% align:start
There's a Zolian camp
on the Nagori plains.

01:19:20.361 --> 01:19:23.030 position:24% line:83% align:start
Mm. You should get
some rest for tomorrow.

01:19:23.063 --> 01:19:24.999 position:7% line:89% align:start
Tell the others to do the same.

01:19:25.032 --> 01:19:26.767 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Sir.
-(horse neighs)

01:19:30.838 --> 01:19:34.942 position:41% line:77% align:start
 <i>OHFAN:</i>
 <i>My people have already left</i>
 <i>the village to go into hiding.</i>

01:19:34.975 --> 01:19:37.244 position:35% line:83% align:start
 <i>Tomorrow,</i>
 <i>everything will change.</i>

01:19:37.278 --> 01:19:40.214 position:30% line:83% align:start
The Zolian army
will swarm in here.

01:19:40.247 --> 01:19:42.483 position:10% line:89% align:start
Even this view will be gone.

01:19:45.019 --> 01:19:47.187 position:24% line:83% align:start
-(Olaha screeches)
-Hey.

01:19:48.889 --> 01:19:51.158 position:24% line:89% align:start
Olaha, what is it?

01:19:53.427 --> 01:19:55.896 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

01:19:55.929 --> 01:19:57.831 position:38% line:89% align:start
(gasping)

01:19:57.865 --> 01:20:00.334 position:21% line:89% align:start
(playful screeching)

01:20:09.943 --> 01:20:11.979 position:27% line:83% align:start
Did you know that
pyuika have the blood

01:20:12.012 --> 01:20:14.315 position:7% line:89% align:start
of Fire Horse Village, as well?

01:20:16.050 --> 01:20:17.619 position:16% line:89% align:start
We forgot all about them.

01:20:17.652 --> 01:20:19.420 position:30% line:83% align:start
Don't even know
how to breed them.

01:20:19.453 --> 01:20:21.989 position:7% line:89% align:start
And yet still they gather here.

01:20:22.022 --> 01:20:25.125 position:24% line:83% align:start
This land is sacred
for the pyuika, too.

01:20:25.159 --> 01:20:27.094 position:16% line:89% align:start
So, then, what do you say

01:20:27.127 --> 01:20:29.363 position:27% line:83% align:start
you and I reclaim
this realm together?

01:20:30.331 --> 01:20:32.600 position:35% line:89% align:start
 <i>Van? Van!</i>

01:20:33.901 --> 01:20:35.469 position:44% line:83% align:start
YUNA:
Pretty, right?

01:20:35.502 --> 01:20:38.105 position:27% line:89% align:start
Right? (chuckles)

01:20:40.174 --> 01:20:41.475 position:33% line:89% align:start
Who are you?

01:20:42.476 --> 01:20:44.278 position:13% line:89% align:start
It's so pretty. (chuckles)

01:20:44.311 --> 01:20:45.547 position:41% line:89% align:start
Pretty?

01:20:45.580 --> 01:20:48.349 position:44% line:83% align:start
YUNA:
Because they glow.

01:20:49.350 --> 01:20:51.385 position:38% line:83% align:start
HOHSALLE:
The asshimi?

01:20:52.453 --> 01:20:53.588 position:35% line:89% align:start
Are you...

01:20:53.621 --> 01:20:55.222 position:41% line:89% align:start
(gasps)

01:20:55.255 --> 01:20:57.191 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yuna.

01:21:05.366 --> 01:21:07.334 position:41% line:83% align:start
-Ossam.
-MAN: I'm sorry,

01:21:07.368 --> 01:21:09.937 position:33% line:83% align:start
but that area
is off-limits to you.

01:21:09.970 --> 01:21:13.140 position:13% line:83% align:start
It's good to see you again,
Sir Hohsalle.

01:21:13.173 --> 01:21:16.143 position:5% line:89% align:start
We studied together in Otawalle.

01:21:16.176 --> 01:21:18.912 position:24% line:89% align:start
My name is Shikan.

01:21:18.946 --> 01:21:21.148 position:7% line:89% align:start
Please, sir, I need your help.

01:21:21.181 --> 01:21:24.151 position:24% line:83% align:start
OHFAN: Last autumn,
the so-called right-hand man

01:21:24.184 --> 01:21:28.055 position:21% line:83% align:start
to the king of Aquafa
paid a visit to this village.

01:21:28.088 --> 01:21:31.925 position:10% line:83% align:start
He said Zolian Emperor Natalu
was going to resume the visit

01:21:31.959 --> 01:21:33.994 position:19% line:89% align:start
of the Emperor's Eyes.

01:21:34.995 --> 01:21:37.965 position:10% line:83% align:start
He said they'd long forgotten
their fear of the mittsual.

01:21:37.998 --> 01:21:39.967 position:21% line:83% align:start
They didn't remember
just how well

01:21:40.000 --> 01:21:41.969 position:13% line:89% align:start
it protected this village.

01:21:42.002 --> 01:21:45.239 position:7% line:83% align:start
That is why Kenoi chose to lead
the ossam once again.

01:21:45.272 --> 01:21:48.142 position:27% line:83% align:start
It was necessary,
to remind the Zolians

01:21:48.175 --> 01:21:50.344 position:13% line:89% align:start
why they should be afraid.

01:21:50.377 --> 01:21:53.080 position:21% line:83% align:start
However, the Dog King
is growing old,

01:21:53.113 --> 01:21:56.283 position:27% line:83% align:start
and his power is
unfortunately waning.

01:21:56.316 --> 01:21:58.185 position:27% line:83% align:start
A successor needs
to take his place

01:21:58.218 --> 01:21:59.953 position:13% line:89% align:start
as the leader of the pack.

01:21:59.987 --> 01:22:02.389 position:21% line:89% align:start
And it cannot be me,

01:22:02.423 --> 01:22:05.959 position:27% line:83% align:start
for the mittsual
has chosen you, Van.

01:22:07.595 --> 01:22:10.130 position:24% line:89% align:start
(shallow breathing)

01:22:10.164 --> 01:22:12.567 position:30% line:83% align:start
What happened?
Was this the mittsual's doing?

01:22:12.600 --> 01:22:14.234 position:41% line:83% align:start
SHIKAN:
Yes.

01:22:14.268 --> 01:22:16.003 position:38% line:83% align:start
HOHSALLE:
But these children--

01:22:16.036 --> 01:22:18.005 position:19% line:83% align:start
-aren't they Aquafaese?
-They are.

01:22:18.038 --> 01:22:20.174 position:21% line:83% align:start
They should have been
immune to it, but they're not.

01:22:20.207 --> 01:22:22.443 position:21% line:83% align:start
They've been infected
as if they were Zolians.

01:22:22.476 --> 01:22:23.578 position:38% line:89% align:start
But why?

01:22:23.611 --> 01:22:25.513 position:30% line:89% align:start
I do not know.

01:22:25.547 --> 01:22:27.715 position:30% line:83% align:start
All of them are
liberated captives from Zol.

01:22:27.749 --> 01:22:31.151 position:7% line:83% align:start
Perhaps it's because they were
raised in Zolian villages.

01:22:31.185 --> 01:22:34.054 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>I can't think of</i>
 <i>any other reason, unless...</i>

01:22:34.087 --> 01:22:36.323 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>maybe the disease has mutated.</i>

01:22:37.592 --> 01:22:39.661 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>HOHSALLE: They were</i>
 <i>bitten by the ossam?</i>

01:22:39.694 --> 01:22:41.228 position:33% line:89% align:start
 <i>SHIKAN: Yes.</i>

01:22:41.261 --> 01:22:44.732 position:16% line:77% align:start
 <i>After Ohfan freed them,</i>
 <i>they wanted to</i>
 <i>repay him for it,</i>

01:22:44.766 --> 01:22:47.134 position:7% line:89% align:start
so they let the dogs bite them.

01:22:47.167 --> 01:22:49.136 position:38% line:89% align:start
Let them?

01:22:49.169 --> 01:22:51.205 position:13% line:89% align:start
Why volunteer to be bitten?

01:22:51.238 --> 01:22:54.074 position:21% line:83% align:start
They wanted the power
to become the next Dog King.

01:22:54.107 --> 01:22:55.342 position:24% line:89% align:start
I don't understand.

01:22:55.375 --> 01:22:57.545 position:41% line:83% align:start
SHIKAN:
The ossam can only be led

01:22:57.579 --> 01:23:00.080 position:16% line:83% align:start
by a human who's survived
one of their bites.

01:23:00.113 --> 01:23:03.518 position:10% line:83% align:start
Someone the mittsual chooses
to bestow with a special power.

01:23:04.519 --> 01:23:07.421 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>VAN: Why was I the one</i>
 <i>to survive this disease?</i>

01:23:07.454 --> 01:23:10.157 position:41% line:83% align:start
(gasps)
Are you talking about Van?

01:23:10.190 --> 01:23:11.626 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yes.

01:23:11.659 --> 01:23:15.262 position:7% line:83% align:start
BOY: Does that mean a successor
has been found?

01:23:15.295 --> 01:23:17.030 position:38% line:89% align:start
We tried.

01:23:17.064 --> 01:23:19.166 position:24% line:89% align:start
We weren't worthy.

01:23:19.199 --> 01:23:20.501 position:30% line:89% align:start
But it's okay.

01:23:20.535 --> 01:23:22.269 position:33% line:89% align:start
He found one.

01:23:22.302 --> 01:23:23.638 position:27% line:89% align:start
Congratulations.

01:23:23.671 --> 01:23:25.272 position:16% line:89% align:start
You did it, Chief Ohfan.

01:23:25.305 --> 01:23:27.775 position:30% line:83% align:start
-(boy coughing)
-(Shikan gasping)

01:23:30.244 --> 01:23:32.079 position:27% line:83% align:start
-Boil some water.
-Huh?

01:23:32.112 --> 01:23:34.516 position:19% line:83% align:start
-Do you have any ikimi?
-A little, yes.

01:23:34.549 --> 01:23:36.784 position:10% line:83% align:start
I'll teach you a combination
to mix it with.

01:23:36.818 --> 01:23:38.753 position:24% line:83% align:start
-Bring your herbs.
-Right.

01:23:38.786 --> 01:23:42.155 position:35% line:83% align:start
 <i>HOHSALLE:</i>
 <i>Damn it. Where are you, Van?</i>

01:23:50.163 --> 01:23:52.332 position:10% line:89% align:start
Hey, newcomer, get a move on!

01:23:52.366 --> 01:23:54.301 position:35% line:89% align:start
(grunting)

01:23:54.334 --> 01:23:55.502 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

01:23:58.138 --> 01:24:00.675 position:27% line:89% align:start
Wait, that woman.

01:24:00.708 --> 01:24:03.243 position:16% line:89% align:start
Hey, the food! Come back!

01:24:04.546 --> 01:24:06.548 position:41% line:83% align:start
TOHLIM:
You disobeyed my order.

01:24:06.581 --> 01:24:08.081 position:44% line:83% align:start
SAE:
Yes.

01:24:08.115 --> 01:24:09.483 position:7% line:89% align:start
His life nullifies everything.

01:24:09.517 --> 01:24:11.285 position:21% line:83% align:start
Letting him go means
the mittsual

01:24:11.318 --> 01:24:13.453 position:10% line:89% align:start
will no longer pose a threat.

01:24:13.487 --> 01:24:16.724 position:13% line:83% align:start
And I don't have to explain
to you what that means for us.

01:24:17.725 --> 01:24:19.326 position:24% line:89% align:start
You disappoint me.

01:24:19.359 --> 01:24:20.662 position:30% line:89% align:start
Take her away.

01:24:20.695 --> 01:24:22.530 position:38% line:83% align:start
SOLDIERS:
Yes, sir.

01:24:25.232 --> 01:24:26.601 position:41% line:89% align:start
Get up.

01:24:31.739 --> 01:24:33.675 position:16% line:83% align:start
That's the tracker woman,
is it not?

01:24:33.708 --> 01:24:37.411 position:16% line:83% align:start
Yes. It appears she lost
the survivor from the salt mine.

01:24:37.444 --> 01:24:39.847 position:35% line:83% align:start
-She what?
-(sighs)

01:24:39.881 --> 01:24:41.716 position:41% line:83% align:start
TOHLIM:
Now all we can do is watch

01:24:41.749 --> 01:24:45.185 position:30% line:83% align:start
as the visit of
the Emperor's Eyes proceeds.

01:24:45.218 --> 01:24:47.354 position:10% line:89% align:start
I'll ensure Ohfan's silence.

01:24:47.387 --> 01:24:50.490 position:5% line:83% align:start
-And abandon Fire Horse Village?
-Yes.

01:24:50.525 --> 01:24:55.262 position:10% line:83% align:start
And grit our teeth as we gaze
upon the emperor's smiling face.

01:24:55.295 --> 01:24:58.131 position:13% line:89% align:start
We sacrifice far too much.

01:25:00.400 --> 01:25:01.703 position:27% line:89% align:start
(Makokan panting)

01:25:01.736 --> 01:25:03.805 position:5% line:89% align:start
You! Tracker woman! Where is he?

01:25:03.838 --> 01:25:06.306 position:16% line:83% align:start
-SOLDIER: What are you...
-Where is Sir Hohsalle?

01:25:06.340 --> 01:25:08.342 position:16% line:89% align:start
Where did you leave him?

01:25:08.375 --> 01:25:09.644 position:24% line:83% align:start
-SOLDIER: Stop it!
-Move!

01:25:09.677 --> 01:25:11.613 position:21% line:83% align:start
I must ask that woman
a question!

01:25:14.582 --> 01:25:17.284 position:33% line:89% align:start
(whimpering)

01:25:17.317 --> 01:25:18.452 position:44% line:89% align:start
Help!

01:25:18.485 --> 01:25:20.220 position:30% line:89% align:start
Hel... (groans)

01:25:24.759 --> 01:25:26.628 position:10% line:89% align:start
By now, Sir Hohsalle and Van

01:25:26.661 --> 01:25:28.863 position:24% line:83% align:start
should have reached
Fire Horse Village.

01:25:28.896 --> 01:25:31.766 position:27% line:83% align:start
Follow the cliffs
three leagues to the north.

01:25:31.799 --> 01:25:34.234 position:16% line:83% align:start
You'll find a secret path
to the village

01:25:34.267 --> 01:25:36.269 position:13% line:89% align:start
hidden in the mountainside.

01:25:50.484 --> 01:25:52.520 position:24% line:89% align:start
(shallow breathing)

01:25:54.956 --> 01:25:57.257 position:24% line:89% align:start
It is morning now.

01:25:57.290 --> 01:25:59.259 position:19% line:89% align:start
Drink this pyuika milk.

01:25:59.292 --> 01:26:01.129 position:21% line:89% align:start
It will nourish you.

01:26:02.229 --> 01:26:04.197 position:5% line:89% align:start
All the villagers here drink it.

01:26:04.231 --> 01:26:07.669 position:16% line:83% align:start
And there was a time when
all the people of Aquafa did.

01:26:07.702 --> 01:26:09.904 position:24% line:83% align:start
These boys grew up
as captives of Zol,

01:26:09.937 --> 01:26:12.940 position:16% line:83% align:start
so they refuse it because
they don't like the smell.

01:26:12.974 --> 01:26:15.677 position:10% line:83% align:start
I wish I could convince them
they need it.

01:26:15.710 --> 01:26:18.311 position:7% line:89% align:start
(gasps) Chief Ohfan is coming.

01:26:28.856 --> 01:26:30.658 position:30% line:89% align:start
There you are.

01:26:33.828 --> 01:26:35.797 position:16% line:83% align:start
You're the sacred doctor,
aren't you?

01:26:35.830 --> 01:26:38.700 position:27% line:83% align:start
You should know,
Van is here for a reason.

01:26:38.733 --> 01:26:41.602 position:7% line:83% align:start
The mittsual brought the former
leader of the Lone Antlers

01:26:41.636 --> 01:26:43.771 position:33% line:83% align:start
to this land
to become its new king.

01:26:43.805 --> 01:26:45.907 position:10% line:89% align:start
That is the will of the gods.

01:26:45.940 --> 01:26:49.911 position:21% line:83% align:start
Only the chosen ones
can survive the disease.

01:26:50.945 --> 01:26:52.980 position:38% line:83% align:start
HOHSALLE:
No! A disease is all it is,

01:26:53.014 --> 01:26:54.982 position:16% line:89% align:start
not the will of the gods.

01:26:55.016 --> 01:26:58.452 position:10% line:83% align:start
With the help of Van's blood,
I can save those children.

01:26:59.654 --> 01:27:01.288 position:33% line:89% align:start
Interesting.

01:27:01.321 --> 01:27:03.624 position:27% line:83% align:start
Then you're here
because you seek Van.

01:27:05.026 --> 01:27:06.594 position:35% line:89% align:start
Very well.

01:27:06.627 --> 01:27:08.696 position:10% line:89% align:start
I suppose all will be decided

01:27:08.730 --> 01:27:10.998 position:24% line:83% align:start
once he has become
the next Dog King.

01:27:11.032 --> 01:27:13.868 position:38% line:83% align:start
Go, Van.
Kenoi's waiting for you.

01:27:13.901 --> 01:27:16.604 position:7% line:83% align:start
-And your daughter is with him.
-HOHSALLE: No.

01:27:16.637 --> 01:27:17.972 position:27% line:89% align:start
Don't do it, Van!

01:27:18.005 --> 01:27:19.507 position:38% line:89% align:start
(grunts)

01:27:26.379 --> 01:27:29.550 position:19% line:83% align:start
It's true. The mittsual
does appear to be godly.

01:27:29.584 --> 01:27:32.620 position:24% line:83% align:start
We can't guess when
or why it'll happen.

01:27:32.653 --> 01:27:36.657 position:10% line:83% align:start
And we don't yet know why it
will spare some but kill others.

01:27:36.691 --> 01:27:39.426 position:33% line:83% align:start
As it stands,
it is far beyond our grasp.

01:27:39.459 --> 01:27:40.695 position:38% line:89% align:start
And yet,

01:27:40.728 --> 01:27:44.031 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>that does not justify</i>
 <i>giving up.</i>

01:27:44.065 --> 01:27:46.634 position:7% line:89% align:start
Perhaps it seems to be destiny,

01:27:46.667 --> 01:27:48.569 position:24% line:83% align:start
but isn't fighting
against destiny

01:27:48.603 --> 01:27:51.271 position:27% line:83% align:start
how we've managed
to survive this long?

01:27:52.073 --> 01:27:56.376 position:16% line:83% align:start
Hmm. Actually, I'm quite
satisfied with my destiny.

01:27:56.409 --> 01:27:58.880 position:35% line:83% align:start
(chuckles)
Zolian Emperor Natalu.

01:27:58.913 --> 01:28:03.316 position:16% line:83% align:start
I'll gladly give my life
to end his.

01:28:08.823 --> 01:28:10.825 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

01:28:15.362 --> 01:28:17.397 position:35% line:89% align:start
(growling)

01:28:21.736 --> 01:28:23.470 position:41% line:83% align:start
 <i>KENOI:</i>
 <i>Are you willing?</i>

01:28:23.503 --> 01:28:25.873 position:27% line:89% align:start
 <i>Answer me, Van.</i>

01:28:25.907 --> 01:28:30.410 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>Amidst the sea of darkness,</i>
 <i>the mittsual found you.</i>

01:28:30.443 --> 01:28:34.615 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>Use it to remake our world</i>
 <i>as the Dog King.</i>

01:28:34.649 --> 01:28:37.919 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>Do that which your soul</i>
 <i>surely desires.</i>

01:28:39.020 --> 01:28:40.855 position:27% line:89% align:start
I lost my family,

01:28:40.888 --> 01:28:44.058 position:19% line:83% align:start
which left me groveling
in the darkness for a long time.

01:28:44.091 --> 01:28:46.393 position:21% line:89% align:start
Until Yuna saved me.

01:28:46.426 --> 01:28:49.096 position:24% line:83% align:start
She brought me back
from the abyss.

01:28:49.130 --> 01:28:51.933 position:21% line:83% align:start
That little girl was
what saved my soul.

01:28:51.966 --> 01:28:53.968 position:35% line:89% align:start
(rumbling)

01:28:55.570 --> 01:28:56.737 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yuna!

01:28:57.939 --> 01:29:01.008 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>KENOI: She is favored</i>
 <i>by the ossam, as well.</i>

01:29:01.042 --> 01:29:05.980 position:35% line:77% align:start
 <i>Like you,</i>
 <i>she has been given the power</i>
 <i>to become their ruler.</i>

01:29:06.013 --> 01:29:08.649 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>This is the answer you seek.</i>

01:29:09.617 --> 01:29:13.020 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>Give in to it, Van.</i>

01:29:13.054 --> 01:29:15.790 position:38% line:83% align:start
-VAN: No.
 <i>-Hmm?</i>

01:29:15.823 --> 01:29:19.359 position:21% line:83% align:start
VAN: This is no place
for her to live.

01:29:20.161 --> 01:29:24.866 position:7% line:83% align:start
And I want to live on with her,
so I must continue to resist.

01:29:26.968 --> 01:29:29.136 position:16% line:89% align:start
I cannot be the Dog King.

01:29:29.170 --> 01:29:31.138 position:41% line:89% align:start
(gasps)

01:29:32.106 --> 01:29:34.909 position:16% line:89% align:start
(Kenoi gasping, wheezing)

01:29:34.942 --> 01:29:37.979 position:41% line:83% align:start
 <i>KENOI:</i>
 <i>Why not?</i>

01:29:39.847 --> 01:29:41.816 position:35% line:89% align:start
(groaning)

01:29:41.849 --> 01:29:44.151 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>If you will not succeed me,</i>

01:29:44.185 --> 01:29:47.154 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>why do you possess that power?</i>

01:29:47.188 --> 01:29:50.157 position:27% line:89% align:start
(Kenoi groaning)

01:30:04.171 --> 01:30:06.406 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

01:30:15.482 --> 01:30:17.151 position:44% line:89% align:start
Dada?

01:30:18.653 --> 01:30:20.554 position:35% line:89% align:start
(Van sighs)

01:30:23.791 --> 01:30:25.660 position:44% line:83% align:start
YUNA:
You came back.

01:30:27.995 --> 01:30:29.664 position:21% line:83% align:start
-(running footsteps)
-Huh?

01:30:29.697 --> 01:30:31.666 position:24% line:89% align:start
(panting, grunting)

01:30:31.699 --> 01:30:33.234 position:33% line:89% align:start
Sir Hohsalle!

01:30:33.267 --> 01:30:34.936 position:41% line:89% align:start
(sighs)

01:30:34.969 --> 01:30:36.737 position:21% line:89% align:start
At last, I found you.

01:30:36.771 --> 01:30:39.640 position:7% line:83% align:start
-You came an awfully long way.
-We have to go.

01:30:39.674 --> 01:30:42.176 position:13% line:83% align:start
This may be the only chance
we have to escape.

01:30:42.209 --> 01:30:44.078 position:27% line:89% align:start
(grunts) Hold on.

01:30:44.111 --> 01:30:46.147 position:16% line:89% align:start
Where is that Van fellow?

01:30:46.180 --> 01:30:47.715 position:35% line:89% align:start
(both gasp)

01:30:50.284 --> 01:30:52.186 position:30% line:83% align:start
-HOHSALLE: Van.
-(Yuna giggles)

01:30:53.187 --> 01:30:55.990 position:21% line:83% align:start
-(Hohsalle chuckles)
